1
00:00:43,750 --> 00:00:45,040
[wind blowing]

2
00:00:46,207 --> 00:00:47,625
[Mufasa]
<i>Look at the stars.</i>

3
00:00:47,790 --> 00:00:49,790
<i>Whenever you feel alone,</i>

4
00:00:49,957 --> 00:00:52,082
<i>the great kings of the past</i>

5
00:00:52,250 --> 00:00:54,957
<i>will always be up there
to guide you.</i>

6
00:00:55,790 --> 00:00:57,125
<i>And so will I.</i>

7
00:01:02,957 --> 00:01:05,957
[♪ majestic song playing
in other language]

8
00:01:20,290 --> 00:01:21,625
[roars]

9
00:01:24,957 --> 00:01:26,250
[trumpets]

10
00:01:46,540 --> 00:01:48,832
- [leaves rustle]
- [birds chirping]

11
00:02:11,332 --> 00:02:12,915
[song ends]

12
00:02:15,415 --> 00:02:19,540
My friends, the time of
my family's growth is upon us.

13
00:02:20,625 --> 00:02:22,998
This home we share
is the fulfillment

14
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,500
of my father's vision.

15
00:02:24,665 --> 00:02:26,748
How wonderful is it
that Nala and I

16
00:02:26,750 --> 00:02:28,665
get to continue his dream

17
00:02:28,832 --> 00:02:31,414
and make even greater
the Circle of Life?

18
00:02:31,415 --> 00:02:32,957
[animals cheer]

19
00:02:38,457 --> 00:02:40,875
Nala, my love, I'm on my way.

20
00:02:42,832 --> 00:02:44,832
[♪ serene music playing]

21
00:03:18,790 --> 00:03:20,457
Simba...

22
00:03:21,207 --> 00:03:22,582
I'm here.

23
00:03:23,957 --> 00:03:25,250
I'm here.

24
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:28,000
[♪ exhilarating song playing
in other language]

25
00:03:36,832 --> 00:03:38,040
[grunts]

26
00:03:38,375 --> 00:03:40,790
[Pumbaa] Security detail
has arrived!

27
00:03:40,957 --> 00:03:43,457
[Timon] One gentle reminder:
we are not food.

28
00:03:43,625 --> 00:03:45,625
No, no, no, no, no.
We are just two guys

29
00:03:45,790 --> 00:03:48,082
walking to work through
a pride of hungry lions.

30
00:03:48,250 --> 00:03:50,957
[Timon] Which is perfectly
normal. I'm not terrified.

31
00:03:51,457 --> 00:03:53,789
Security detail
reporting for duty,

32
00:03:53,790 --> 00:03:55,500
Your Grace, Your Highness...

33
00:03:55,665 --> 00:03:58,082
Ruler of all
four-legged creatures.

34
00:03:58,250 --> 00:04:00,457
And that one three-legged zebra.

35
00:04:00,625 --> 00:04:02,875
Oh, right, Ron.
That was tragic.

36
00:04:03,040 --> 00:04:04,332
- It was an eat-and-Ron.
- Yeah.

37
00:04:04,500 --> 00:04:06,414
Ron has three legs.
That's still one more than me.

38
00:04:06,415 --> 00:04:07,623
- Well, are those arms or legs?
- [Simba] Guys.

39
00:04:07,625 --> 00:04:08,706
I don't know.
I think they're paws.

40
00:04:08,707 --> 00:04:09,789
[Simba] Guys.

41
00:04:09,790 --> 00:04:12,415
- I consider all those legs.
- Guys! This is serious.

42
00:04:12,582 --> 00:04:14,500
I need you to stay with Kiara
until I get back.

43
00:04:14,665 --> 00:04:17,415
Are you saying
that your security detail

44
00:04:17,415 --> 00:04:20,290
has been called on
to do babysitting?

45
00:04:20,457 --> 00:04:21,874
Pumbaa, we should
really discuss this

46
00:04:21,875 --> 00:04:23,375
because I don't really love...

47
00:04:23,540 --> 00:04:26,000
Guys, I promised her
everything would be okay.

48
00:04:26,165 --> 00:04:27,290
Well, that's one way to parent.

49
00:04:27,457 --> 00:04:28,500
She's gonna
have to grow up sometime.

50
00:04:28,665 --> 00:04:29,665
What else did you tell her,

51
00:04:29,665 --> 00:04:31,250
that she could be
whatever she wants to be?

52
00:04:31,415 --> 00:04:32,457
That life is fair?

53
00:04:32,625 --> 00:04:34,915
I need you two to try
and act like adults, okay?

54
00:04:35,082 --> 00:04:38,125
Don't scare Kiara.
And most of all, no stories.

55
00:04:38,290 --> 00:04:39,749
- No stories?
- Wait a second.

56
00:04:39,750 --> 00:04:40,831
I know where your head goes.

57
00:04:40,832 --> 00:04:42,457
I grew up with you two.
Promise me.

58
00:04:42,625 --> 00:04:43,999
Okay. You know what,
you know what, you know what?

59
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,415
Fine. No stories.

60
00:04:45,582 --> 00:04:46,957
Speak for yourself, Pumbaa.

61
00:04:47,125 --> 00:04:49,165
No. Pssh. [whispers]
We'll tell a story anyway.

62
00:04:49,165 --> 00:04:50,415
[whispers] Okay, we'll tell
him that we're not gonna

63
00:04:50,415 --> 00:04:51,499
tell a story and then
we're gonna tell a story.

64
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:52,790
- He can't stop us.
- Are you guys serious?

65
00:04:52,957 --> 00:04:54,500
I'm clearly within earshot.

66
00:04:54,665 --> 00:04:55,790
Dad. [panting]

67
00:04:58,707 --> 00:05:00,333
- Hey, little one.
- [coos]

68
00:05:01,790 --> 00:05:04,165
Dad, the storm's coming,
and I'm scared.

69
00:05:04,333 --> 00:05:05,833
I wanna go with you and Mom.

70
00:05:06,165 --> 00:05:07,540
- Don't be scared, my love.
- Mmm.

71
00:05:07,750 --> 00:05:09,750
Timon and Pumbaa
will watch you while I'm gone.

72
00:05:09,915 --> 00:05:11,375
Be brave now, Kiara.

73
00:05:12,208 --> 00:05:14,000
Be brave.

74
00:05:18,457 --> 00:05:21,081
[in normal voice] Okay!
We've prepared a story.

75
00:05:21,082 --> 00:05:23,165
[♪ dramatic music playing]

76
00:05:23,332 --> 00:05:24,625
[Timon] <i>Scar looked at us.</i>

77
00:05:24,790 --> 00:05:26,875
<i>He knew it was
the end of the line.</i>

78
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,875
<i>I could smell the fear.</i>

79
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:31,165
[Pumbaa] <i>That was actually me,
but yes.</i>

80
00:05:33,832 --> 00:05:35,000
[roars]

81
00:05:37,457 --> 00:05:38,457
[grunts]

82
00:05:48,832 --> 00:05:50,790
[Kiara] <i>So you two
defeated Scar?</i>

83
00:05:50,957 --> 00:05:52,040
And then you ate him?

84
00:05:52,207 --> 00:05:54,207
Honestly, one of the best
meals I ever had.

85
00:05:54,375 --> 00:05:56,290
My dad told me he defeated Scar.

86
00:05:56,457 --> 00:05:57,831
Well, okay. But your dad,

87
00:05:57,832 --> 00:05:59,415
as we all know,
is a pathological liar.

88
00:05:59,582 --> 00:06:01,665
He's always lyin'. Get it?

89
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,040
- [thunder rumbles]
- [gasps]

90
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:04,165
[elephants trumpet]

91
00:06:05,290 --> 00:06:07,333
I'm scared.
I want Mom and Dad.

92
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:08,625
[Pumbaa] Look, look, look
look, look.

93
00:06:08,790 --> 00:06:10,415
Don't be scared, Kiara.

94
00:06:10,583 --> 00:06:14,000
How about we sing you a song?
And, a-one...

95
00:06:14,165 --> 00:06:16,665
Pumbaa, no, it is
way too early for the song.

96
00:06:16,832 --> 00:06:17,831
It worked on Simba.

97
00:06:17,832 --> 00:06:19,290
He thought he had
murdered his own father.

98
00:06:19,457 --> 00:06:21,290
He was singin' and dancin'
around in seconds.

99
00:06:21,457 --> 00:06:22,874
I can't just
turn it on like that.

100
00:06:22,875 --> 00:06:24,415
I have to be in the moment.

101
00:06:24,582 --> 00:06:25,790
He sang that song
for six years straight.

102
00:06:25,957 --> 00:06:27,375
- Well, who didn't?
- [thunder rumbles]

103
00:06:27,540 --> 00:06:28,665
- Look!
- [Timon screams]

104
00:06:28,665 --> 00:06:29,874
- No!
- It's Ron,

105
00:06:29,875 --> 00:06:31,956
the three-legged zebra.
Run for your lives!

106
00:06:31,957 --> 00:06:33,332
He heard what we've been
sayin' about him.

107
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:36,290
We're sorry, Ron. They were
jokes. They were just jokes!

108
00:06:36,665 --> 00:06:37,915
[Kiara] It's Rafiki.

109
00:06:38,082 --> 00:06:39,915
Rafiki! Rafiki!

110
00:06:39,915 --> 00:06:41,457
[laughs]

111
00:06:42,250 --> 00:06:44,832
Little one,
there's no reason to cry.

112
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,000
My parents...

113
00:06:46,540 --> 00:06:47,540
they're gone.

114
00:06:47,540 --> 00:06:50,207
Hey. Look out there, <i>mdogo.</i>

115
00:06:50,707 --> 00:06:53,250
You see those baobab trees
blowing in the wind?

116
00:06:53,750 --> 00:06:58,040
The roots of those trees are
very strong, like your family.

117
00:06:58,207 --> 00:07:00,083
And, just as they did for you,

118
00:07:00,250 --> 00:07:03,750
your parents have gone to the
ceremonial birthing grounds.

119
00:07:03,915 --> 00:07:06,915
And when they return,
the Circle of Life

120
00:07:06,915 --> 00:07:10,040
will bring a blessing
to you, Kiara,

121
00:07:10,208 --> 00:07:12,540
that you will never forget.

122
00:07:12,540 --> 00:07:13,624
[softly] Man, he's good.

123
00:07:13,625 --> 00:07:15,458
He's such a visual storyteller.

124
00:07:15,625 --> 00:07:17,707
Yet it makes sense
that he lives alone.

125
00:07:18,750 --> 00:07:20,749
I just want the storm to pass,

126
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:22,999
and then I promise to be brave.

127
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:25,707
[Rafiki laughs]
I'll tell you a secret.

128
00:07:25,875 --> 00:07:28,250
When your father Simba
was your age,

129
00:07:28,415 --> 00:07:30,249
he was afraid of the thunder

130
00:07:30,250 --> 00:07:32,250
and would hide behind the king.

131
00:07:32,415 --> 00:07:33,625
When did he stop hiding?

132
00:07:33,790 --> 00:07:35,875
One day, during a big storm,

133
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:38,790
your grandfather Mufasa
took your father

134
00:07:38,790 --> 00:07:41,165
to the very top of Pride Rock,

135
00:07:41,332 --> 00:07:42,832
told him to stand with him

136
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,875
and howl into the wind.

137
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:47,832
And Simba slowly stepped out
with the king.

138
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:51,332
And together,
they roared into the night.

139
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,331
[gasps]

140
00:07:53,332 --> 00:07:55,165
But I'm not brave like my dad.

141
00:07:55,707 --> 00:07:57,665
And I could never be
like Mufasa.

142
00:07:57,665 --> 00:08:00,458
[Rafiki chuckling] Is that so?

143
00:08:01,375 --> 00:08:04,165
Then maybe it's time
I tell you a story.

144
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:07,458
A story of a cub,
not much bigger than you.

145
00:08:07,750 --> 00:08:11,125
A lion born without a drop
of nobility in his blood.

146
00:08:11,583 --> 00:08:15,125
A lion who would change
our lives forever.

147
00:08:15,665 --> 00:08:17,832
A story! So glad
I brought some crickets.

148
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,707
But go easy. We're in a cave.

149
00:08:20,250 --> 00:08:22,500
[Rafiki] This story
begins far beyond

150
00:08:22,665 --> 00:08:24,500
the mountains and the shadows.

151
00:08:24,665 --> 00:08:26,457
On the other side of the light.

152
00:08:26,625 --> 00:08:30,875
In this place, everything
was dying of thirst

153
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:33,289
as 20 full moons
had passed without

154
00:08:33,290 --> 00:08:35,540
- a single drop of water.
- [gasps]

155
00:08:35,750 --> 00:08:38,457
But when the skies
finally opened,

156
00:08:39,207 --> 00:08:41,875
- destiny would reign.
- [♪ majestic music playing]

157
00:09:04,082 --> 00:09:05,707
[chittering]

158
00:09:10,625 --> 00:09:11,625
[lioness] Mufasa.

159
00:09:12,666 --> 00:09:15,207
Mufasa! Come see.

160
00:09:21,041 --> 00:09:23,832
Mom, what is that light
way out there?

161
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:26,666
Oh, that's very special.

162
00:09:26,832 --> 00:09:28,457
Beyond the horizon,

163
00:09:28,625 --> 00:09:31,750
beyond the last cloud
in the sky,

164
00:09:31,916 --> 00:09:34,707
that's a place we call <i>Milele.</i>

165
00:09:34,875 --> 00:09:35,915
<i>Milele?</i>

166
00:09:36,082 --> 00:09:38,375
Hmm. It means, "forever."

167
00:09:39,290 --> 00:09:41,625
[lion] Imagine
a kingdom full of life,

168
00:09:42,457 --> 00:09:44,415
water and food,

169
00:09:44,582 --> 00:09:48,375
grass and sky
as far as the eye can see.

170
00:09:48,540 --> 00:09:49,665
Will we ever go there?

171
00:09:49,832 --> 00:09:51,290
Oh, yes, Mufasa.

172
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:53,457
That's exactly
where we're headed.

173
00:09:53,832 --> 00:09:56,625
But we can also
be there right now.

174
00:09:57,040 --> 00:09:58,707
We can close our eyes.

175
00:09:58,875 --> 00:10:01,166
Let our dreams take us.

176
00:10:01,332 --> 00:10:02,706
- [♪ enthralling song playing]
- [chorus] <i>♪ Sekuseduzani ♪</i>

177
00:10:02,707 --> 00:10:04,124
<i>♪ Empumalanga ♪</i>

178
00:10:04,125 --> 00:10:07,500
<i>♪ Entshonalanga
Sala ngoxolo ♪</i>

179
00:10:07,957 --> 00:10:11,166
[lioness] <i>♪ Beyond
the horizon ♪</i>

180
00:10:11,332 --> 00:10:15,041
<i>♪ Beyond the last cloud
in the sky ♪</i>

181
00:10:15,750 --> 00:10:18,707
<i>♪ There's a place I know ♪</i>

182
00:10:19,625 --> 00:10:21,749
[chorus] <i>♪ Siqhubek'ekhaya
s'ofika ♪</i>

183
00:10:21,750 --> 00:10:23,499
<i>- ♪ Ngothando ♪</i>
- [lioness] <i>♪ Imagine ♪</i>

184
00:10:23,500 --> 00:10:25,166
<i>- ♪ A kingdom ♪
- </i> [chorus] <i>♪ Ngothando ♪</i>

185
00:10:25,332 --> 00:10:27,081
[lioness] <i>♪ The water flows ♪</i>

186
00:10:27,082 --> 00:10:29,332
<i>- ♪ The grass is high ♪</i>
- [chorus] <i>♪ S'ofika ♪</i>

187
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:32,125
- <i>♪ It's not a dream ♪
- </i> [chorus] <i>♪ Ngothando! ♪</i>

188
00:10:32,250 --> 00:10:35,250
<i>♪ Someday we'll go ♪</i>

189
00:10:35,875 --> 00:10:39,289
<i>- ♪ We call it ♪
- </i> [chorus] <i>♪ Tunaita ♪</i>

190
00:10:39,290 --> 00:10:41,081
<i>- ♪ Milele ♪
- ♪ Sivulele indlela ♪</i>

191
00:10:41,082 --> 00:10:42,749
<i>♪ S'yacela Milele ♪</i>

192
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:44,789
<i>- ♪ It's always there ♪
- ♪ Sivulele indlela ♪</i>

193
00:10:44,790 --> 00:10:46,081
<i>♪ Somandla!
Daimaiko ♪</i>

194
00:10:46,082 --> 00:10:48,289
<i>- ♪ Milele ♪
- ♪ Sivulele indlela ♪</i>

195
00:10:48,290 --> 00:10:51,249
<i>- ♪ S'yacela Milele ♪
- ♪ It lives in you ♪</i>

196
00:10:51,250 --> 00:10:53,832
<i>- ♪ It lives in me ♪
- ♪ Siqonde Phambile ♪</i>

197
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:56,750
<i>- ♪ You'll see ♪
- ♪ Milele! ♪</i>

198
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,706
<i>♪ Life, great and small ♪</i>

199
00:10:59,707 --> 00:11:01,500
<i>♪ The Circle of Life
is not small ♪</i>

200
00:11:01,832 --> 00:11:04,374
<i>♪ We know that
there's enough for all ♪</i>

201
00:11:04,375 --> 00:11:05,666
[lion] <i>♪ There's enough
for all ♪</i>

202
00:11:06,082 --> 00:11:09,291
[both] <i>♪ There
is always more ♪</i>

203
00:11:09,457 --> 00:11:10,499
[lioness] <i>♪ Can you feel it? ♪</i>

204
00:11:10,500 --> 00:11:11,666
[lion] <i>♪ Can you feel it? ♪</i>

205
00:11:11,832 --> 00:11:15,582
<i>- ♪ We're on your side ♪
- ♪ We'll wander no longer ♪</i>

206
00:11:15,750 --> 00:11:17,374
<i>♪ We carry ancestors inside ♪</i>

207
00:11:17,375 --> 00:11:19,166
<i>- ♪ Like a constant tide ♪
- </i> [chorus] <i>♪ S'ofika ♪</i>

208
00:11:19,332 --> 00:11:21,249
<i>♪ It's not a dream,
can you see it? ♪</i>

209
00:11:21,250 --> 00:11:22,749
<i>- ♪ On an endless shore ♪
- ♪ Ngothando! ♪</i>

210
00:11:22,750 --> 00:11:24,249
<i>- ♪ And as you grow ♪
- ♪ Iyhooo! ♪</i>

211
00:11:24,250 --> 00:11:26,166
<i>- ♪ Can you find your way? ♪
- ♪ Can you see it? ♪</i>

212
00:11:26,332 --> 00:11:28,164
- [lion] <i>♪ We call it ♪
- ♪ Sekuseduzani ♪</i>

213
00:11:28,166 --> 00:11:29,624
- [♪ music soars]
<i>- ♪ Tunaita ♪</i>

214
00:11:29,625 --> 00:11:32,124
- [both] <i>♪ Milele ♪
- ♪ Sekuseduzani ♪</i>

215
00:11:32,125 --> 00:11:33,249
<i>♪ Milele! ♪</i>

216
00:11:33,250 --> 00:11:36,415
<i>- ♪ It's always there ♪
- ♪ Sekuseduzani daimaiko ♪</i>

217
00:11:36,582 --> 00:11:38,539
<i>- ♪ Milele ♪
- ♪ Empumalanga entshonalanga ♪</i>

218
00:11:38,540 --> 00:11:40,124
<i>♪ Sala ngoxolo
Milele! ♪</i>

219
00:11:40,125 --> 00:11:43,039
<i>- ♪ We call it ♪
- ♪ Sekuseduzani tunaita ♪</i>

220
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:45,581
<i>- ♪ Empumalanga entshonalanga ♪
- ♪ Milele ♪</i>

221
00:11:45,582 --> 00:11:47,124
<i>♪ Sala ngoxolo
Milele! ♪</i>

222
00:11:47,125 --> 00:11:50,331
- <i>♪ It's always there ♪
- ♪ Sekuseduzani daimaiko ♪</i>

223
00:11:50,332 --> 00:11:51,831
<i>- ♪ Milele ♪
- ♪ Milele! ♪</i>

224
00:11:51,832 --> 00:11:53,874
<i>♪ Empumalanga entshonalanga
Sala ngoxolo ♪</i>

225
00:11:53,875 --> 00:11:55,539
<i>- ♪ Milele! ♪
- ♪ It lives in you ♪</i>

226
00:11:55,540 --> 00:11:58,040
<i>- ♪ It lives in me ♪
- ♪ Sala ngoxolo ♪</i>

227
00:11:58,415 --> 00:12:00,125
<i>- ♪ We're free ♪
- ♪ Ngoxolo ♪</i>

228
00:12:00,291 --> 00:12:06,249
- <i>♪ Milele ♪
- ♪ Milele! ♪</i>

229
00:12:06,250 --> 00:12:07,499
[song fades]

230
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:08,582
[softly] Wow.

231
00:12:15,791 --> 00:12:16,791
What is this?

232
00:12:16,957 --> 00:12:18,916
Rain. Rain!

233
00:12:19,082 --> 00:12:21,206
Oh, finally we have rain!

234
00:12:21,207 --> 00:12:22,875
[animals chittering]

235
00:12:24,541 --> 00:12:27,789
- Dad, race you to the light!
- [lion laughs]

236
00:12:27,791 --> 00:12:29,041
You're too fast.

237
00:12:29,416 --> 00:12:30,791
I've never beaten you.

238
00:12:30,957 --> 00:12:32,707
Nobody has ever beaten you.

239
00:12:33,540 --> 00:12:34,540
[Mufasa] I know!

240
00:12:35,125 --> 00:12:39,039
[lion chuckles] Mufasa!
Fastest cub in the world.

241
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:40,914
[Mufasa laughing]

242
00:12:40,915 --> 00:12:42,375
[animals exclaiming]

243
00:12:48,790 --> 00:12:50,250
[laughing]

244
00:12:53,457 --> 00:12:54,707
[trumpets]

245
00:12:59,415 --> 00:13:00,749
[bellows]

246
00:13:00,750 --> 00:13:02,125
[Mufasa chuckles]

247
00:13:03,082 --> 00:13:04,291
[grunting]

248
00:13:09,166 --> 00:13:10,416
Thank you.

249
00:13:11,916 --> 00:13:13,166
[lioness] Mufasa...

250
00:13:13,291 --> 00:13:14,289
that's enough.

251
00:13:14,291 --> 00:13:17,000
- Mufasa, come back now.
- [animals clamoring]

252
00:13:18,082 --> 00:13:20,250
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

253
00:13:24,082 --> 00:13:26,250
Mufasa, stay there!
I'm coming, son.

254
00:13:27,916 --> 00:13:29,332
[bleating]

255
00:13:32,457 --> 00:13:34,457
[♪ dramatic music playing]

256
00:13:40,665 --> 00:13:42,457
- [Mufasa] Father!
- Mufasa!

257
00:13:47,750 --> 00:13:48,832
[growls]

258
00:13:49,250 --> 00:13:50,250
Mufasa?

259
00:13:51,207 --> 00:13:52,875
I'll catch you on the turn.

260
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:54,457
Find my voice.

261
00:13:54,707 --> 00:13:56,250
Find my voice!

262
00:13:56,415 --> 00:13:57,582
- Mom!
- [lioness screams]

263
00:14:06,875 --> 00:14:10,207
Mufasa, the cliff is too high,
but you can cross at the dam.

264
00:14:10,375 --> 00:14:12,582
Come on, Mufasa,
you can do this.

265
00:14:12,750 --> 00:14:14,291
Find your mother's voice.

266
00:14:14,457 --> 00:14:16,291
[lioness] Listen
to your father, Mufasa!

267
00:14:16,457 --> 00:14:17,791
Listen to us!

268
00:14:20,832 --> 00:14:21,875
[lion] Afia, he's there.

269
00:14:22,541 --> 00:14:24,166
- [Mufasa] Mom!
- [lion] He's there!

270
00:14:24,625 --> 00:14:26,125
- [Mufasa] Mother!
- Mufasa!

271
00:14:27,082 --> 00:14:28,332
[groans]

272
00:14:28,750 --> 00:14:30,957
Find your footing
one step at a time.

273
00:14:31,125 --> 00:14:32,456
- [stutters] I can't.
- You can do this.

274
00:14:32,457 --> 00:14:33,707
I'm right here.

275
00:14:38,665 --> 00:14:41,750
[breathing heavily]

276
00:14:42,415 --> 00:14:43,500
[elephant trumpets]

277
00:14:47,582 --> 00:14:49,165
[Afia screams] Mufasa!

278
00:14:57,082 --> 00:14:58,707
[gasping]

279
00:15:07,832 --> 00:15:09,832
[♪ intriguing music playing]

280
00:15:26,541 --> 00:15:27,875
[gasps]

281
00:15:31,625 --> 00:15:33,082
[hippo grunting]

282
00:15:35,750 --> 00:15:38,040
- [exclaims]
- [laughs]

283
00:15:41,915 --> 00:15:43,790
Mom? [panting]

284
00:15:44,415 --> 00:15:45,415
Dad?

285
00:15:46,500 --> 00:15:47,582
Can you hear me?

286
00:15:49,250 --> 00:15:50,375
Is anyone out there?

287
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:55,000
Mom?

288
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:58,082
[voice fading] Please.

289
00:15:59,582 --> 00:16:00,750
I'm scared.

290
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:03,625
I'm scared.

291
00:16:07,666 --> 00:16:10,541
[Rafiki] <i>The floodwaters
joined a distant river,</i>

292
00:16:10,707 --> 00:16:14,457
<i>carried Mufasa far
from his mother and father.</i>

293
00:16:14,625 --> 00:16:16,750
<i>Beyond all that he knew.</i>

294
00:16:18,457 --> 00:16:20,456
[animals grunting, chittering]

295
00:16:20,457 --> 00:16:22,541
[♪ solemn music playing]

296
00:16:25,582 --> 00:16:27,082
[birds chirping]

297
00:16:36,875 --> 00:16:38,915
[whimpering]

298
00:16:44,290 --> 00:16:46,206
- [lion cub] Hello.
- [gasps]

299
00:16:46,207 --> 00:16:49,165
I'm Taka, son of Obasi.
What's your name?

300
00:16:49,332 --> 00:16:50,457
Mufasa.

301
00:16:50,625 --> 00:16:52,332
I'm not allowed
to talk to Outsiders,

302
00:16:52,500 --> 00:16:54,207
but I have a secret...

303
00:16:54,375 --> 00:16:56,375
[chuckles] ...and I really
want to tell you.

304
00:16:56,540 --> 00:16:58,375
- What's the secret?
- [Taka] I'll get in trouble.

305
00:16:58,540 --> 00:16:59,540
Please, just tell me.

306
00:16:59,665 --> 00:17:01,332
Uh... I don't know.

307
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:02,541
Just tell me!

308
00:17:02,707 --> 00:17:04,874
Okay.
You're about to be eaten.

309
00:17:04,875 --> 00:17:06,458
- [gasps]
- [growling]

310
00:17:07,625 --> 00:17:09,250
I hate secrets!

311
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:12,540
- Swim!
- But I can't!

312
00:17:12,708 --> 00:17:14,333
- You have to swim.
- I don't know how!

313
00:17:14,583 --> 00:17:17,583
All right. Chin up, then walk
underwater really fast.

314
00:17:17,750 --> 00:17:18,958
[stutters] I can't!

315
00:17:19,125 --> 00:17:21,583
- Come on, Mufasa. Faster!
- [straining]

316
00:17:23,290 --> 00:17:25,290
Help me, Taka! Help me!

317
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,208
[whines]

318
00:17:30,500 --> 00:17:31,500
[roaring]

319
00:17:36,208 --> 00:17:37,583
[both chuckling]

320
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:40,375
I told you to wait for me.

321
00:17:40,540 --> 00:17:41,833
It's not my fault, Mum.

322
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:44,500
I came down for a drink
and saw him floating by.

323
00:17:44,665 --> 00:17:46,625
- I'd like you to meet Mufasa.
- [lioness groans]

324
00:17:46,790 --> 00:17:48,499
You're lucky
those crocs were young

325
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:50,290
and afraid to fight. Let's go!

326
00:17:50,458 --> 00:17:51,958
We can't just leave him here.

327
00:17:52,208 --> 00:17:53,875
Rules are rules, Taka.

328
00:17:54,040 --> 00:17:56,375
Obasi will never accept a stray.

329
00:17:56,540 --> 00:18:00,290
I'm not a stray.
I'm just... lost.

330
00:18:00,458 --> 00:18:01,458
See?

331
00:18:02,375 --> 00:18:03,875
He's just lost.

332
00:18:04,915 --> 00:18:06,290
[Mufasa] There was a...
a flood.

333
00:18:07,208 --> 00:18:09,083
My parents,
they tried to save me.

334
00:18:12,040 --> 00:18:13,665
Do you know which way is home?

335
00:18:15,458 --> 00:18:16,540
[lioness] Home?

336
00:18:16,790 --> 00:18:19,665
To be lost is to learn the way.

337
00:18:20,583 --> 00:18:21,750
Call me Eshe.

338
00:18:21,915 --> 00:18:23,000
I'm tired, Eshe.

339
00:18:23,583 --> 00:18:25,124
Come on, it's this way.

340
00:18:25,125 --> 00:18:27,208
[♪ intriguing music playing]

341
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:43,958
- [Taka] Come on, Mufasa.
- [grunts]

342
00:18:52,915 --> 00:18:54,958
[Mufasa] Is this <i>Milele?</i>

343
00:18:55,833 --> 00:18:57,165
[Eshe] No, my love.

344
00:18:58,040 --> 00:18:59,375
[Obasi growls]

345
00:19:03,083 --> 00:19:05,083
I was trying to nap, Eshe.

346
00:19:05,250 --> 00:19:07,583
The all-important nap of kings,

347
00:19:07,750 --> 00:19:10,375
only to be awoken
by the disgusting,

348
00:19:10,540 --> 00:19:13,125
hideous, revolting stench
of a stray.

349
00:19:13,290 --> 00:19:14,415
When we come upon an Outsider,

350
00:19:14,583 --> 00:19:16,958
tell me, what do we do?

351
00:19:17,125 --> 00:19:18,875
Obasi, I know.

352
00:19:19,040 --> 00:19:20,040
Eat it.

353
00:19:20,208 --> 00:19:22,958
But I found him, Dad.
I saved his life.

354
00:19:23,125 --> 00:19:26,665
Taka, we do not associate
with Outsiders.

355
00:19:26,833 --> 00:19:29,665
The only true bond is blood.

356
00:19:29,833 --> 00:19:32,750
I've heard stories of lions
twice our size.

357
00:19:32,915 --> 00:19:34,500
These Outsiders

358
00:19:34,665 --> 00:19:37,040
will devour everything
in their path.

359
00:19:37,290 --> 00:19:39,708
Does he look like he's going
to devour you?

360
00:19:39,875 --> 00:19:40,874
[whimpers]

361
00:19:40,875 --> 00:19:43,790
Whoa, that smell is disgusting.

362
00:19:43,958 --> 00:19:46,125
I'm not even sure I could eat
this <i>kibeti!</i>

363
00:19:46,290 --> 00:19:48,208
I'm not a <i>kibeti.</i>
I'm a Mufasa.

364
00:19:48,375 --> 00:19:50,374
Do you even know
what "Mufasa" means?

365
00:19:50,375 --> 00:19:51,833
- [Mufasa] No.
- It means, "king."

366
00:19:52,290 --> 00:19:53,415
And that's me.

367
00:19:53,583 --> 00:19:56,000
You better start running,
little Mufasa,

368
00:19:56,165 --> 00:19:57,165
for your life.

369
00:19:57,333 --> 00:19:59,375
If I run, you'll never catch me.

370
00:19:59,540 --> 00:20:01,000
I'm the fastest cub
that ever lived.

371
00:20:01,165 --> 00:20:02,207
My father told me so.

372
00:20:02,208 --> 00:20:04,915
[Obasi] Ooh, Taka,
you have a challenge.

373
00:20:05,083 --> 00:20:07,625
They will race
to the dead tree and back.

374
00:20:07,790 --> 00:20:09,750
And when the prince defeats him,

375
00:20:09,915 --> 00:20:12,375
I will finish him in one bite.

376
00:20:12,540 --> 00:20:14,500
What if Mufasa wins?

377
00:20:14,708 --> 00:20:17,958
If he wins, he lives, Obasi.

378
00:20:18,165 --> 00:20:19,333
He stays with me.

379
00:20:20,125 --> 00:20:21,290
You have my word.

380
00:20:23,208 --> 00:20:25,833
Let the race begin!

381
00:20:26,540 --> 00:20:28,583
Ooh, clumsy little stray.

382
00:20:28,958 --> 00:20:30,165
Run, Mufasa!

383
00:20:30,625 --> 00:20:31,915
You did not have to do that.

384
00:20:32,083 --> 00:20:33,915
[Obasi] Taka is the future king.

385
00:20:34,083 --> 00:20:36,000
He has to win
his first challenge.

386
00:20:36,165 --> 00:20:39,375
No, Obasi. To be a true king,
he must earn it.

387
00:20:39,540 --> 00:20:41,040
Don't take that away from him.

388
00:20:43,083 --> 00:20:45,083
[♪ dramatic music playing]

389
00:20:55,250 --> 00:20:56,250
[Mufasa grunts]

390
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:01,665
[gasping, coughing]

391
00:21:10,375 --> 00:21:11,790
[panting]

392
00:21:23,665 --> 00:21:24,958
[♪ music soars]

393
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:33,708
[whines]

394
00:21:36,125 --> 00:21:37,540
[both grunt]

395
00:21:38,415 --> 00:21:39,415
Better hurry.

396
00:21:46,125 --> 00:21:48,000
[♪ enthralling music playing]

397
00:22:02,790 --> 00:22:04,540
I have one more secret, Mufasa.

398
00:22:06,665 --> 00:22:08,165
I always wanted a brother.

399
00:22:23,040 --> 00:22:24,790
- [growls]
- [both laughing]

400
00:22:26,040 --> 00:22:27,958
- Cheater!
- Obasi!

401
00:22:28,125 --> 00:22:31,000
You will keep him
with the females.

402
00:22:31,165 --> 00:22:36,500
Taka, how could you lose
to a stray? [growls]

403
00:22:37,415 --> 00:22:38,583
Well done, Taka.

404
00:22:38,750 --> 00:22:40,540
- Well done.
- [chuckles]

405
00:22:41,375 --> 00:22:42,790
I thought you said
you were fast.

406
00:22:42,958 --> 00:22:44,039
I had to let you win.

407
00:22:44,040 --> 00:22:45,124
Well, I did just go days

408
00:22:45,125 --> 00:22:46,207
with no sleep
while riding the waves of...

409
00:22:46,208 --> 00:22:48,832
Anyway, come on, Mufasa.
Let's get in some trouble.

410
00:22:48,833 --> 00:22:50,915
[♪ joyful music playing]

411
00:22:51,958 --> 00:22:53,625
[Taka] <i>♪ When I am king ♪</i>

412
00:22:53,790 --> 00:22:56,958
<i>♪ No other animal will break
my stride ♪</i>

413
00:22:57,125 --> 00:22:58,875
<i>♪ Break my stride ♪</i>

414
00:22:59,500 --> 00:23:01,333
<i>- ♪ And my brother ♪
- ♪ My brother ♪</i>

415
00:23:01,500 --> 00:23:04,208
<i>♪ When I'm king,
you'll always take my side ♪</i>

416
00:23:04,750 --> 00:23:07,290
<i>- ♪ Ha! Yeah, right ♪
- ♪ That's right ♪</i>

417
00:23:07,458 --> 00:23:09,290
<i>- ♪ When I am king ♪
- ♪ When you are king ♪</i>

418
00:23:09,458 --> 00:23:12,208
<i>♪ No other animal will break
our pride ♪</i>

419
00:23:12,625 --> 00:23:14,540
<i>♪ Break our pride ♪</i>

420
00:23:14,708 --> 00:23:16,625
<i>- ♪ And my brother ♪
- ♪ My brother ♪</i>

421
00:23:16,958 --> 00:23:19,958
<i>♪ Our prey may run away,
but they can't hide ♪</i>

422
00:23:20,375 --> 00:23:21,833
<i>♪ Watch your hide ♪</i>

423
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:23,500
<i>♪ Let's go, let's go ♪</i>

424
00:23:23,665 --> 00:23:24,708
[both] <i>♪ Let's go ♪</i>

425
00:23:24,875 --> 00:23:29,375
<i>♪ Hey, did your mama say
you could be up this late? ♪</i>

426
00:23:29,540 --> 00:23:31,208
<i>♪ Okay, she didn't say
either way ♪</i>

427
00:23:31,375 --> 00:23:32,540
<i>♪ Hide away, let's go ♪</i>

428
00:23:32,708 --> 00:23:37,000
<i>♪ Hey, did your father say
you could be out this far? ♪</i>

429
00:23:37,165 --> 00:23:38,290
<i>♪ Okay, we're on our way ♪</i>

430
00:23:38,458 --> 00:23:40,125
[both] <i>♪ On our way, run away
Let's go ♪</i>

431
00:23:40,290 --> 00:23:44,833
<i>♪ Hey, did your mama say
you could be up this late? ♪</i>

432
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:46,083
[Taka] <i>♪ Ha ha,
you're very sharp ♪</i>

433
00:23:46,250 --> 00:23:47,833
<i>♪ Yes, you are,
yes, you are, let's go ♪</i>

434
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:52,750
<i>♪ Hey, did your father say
you could be out this far? ♪</i>

435
00:23:53,250 --> 00:23:54,332
<i>♪ Make a wish
on the brightest star ♪</i>

436
00:23:54,333 --> 00:23:55,415
<i>♪ And I say ♪</i>

437
00:23:55,583 --> 00:23:59,208
<i>♪ I always wanted a brother
I always wanted a brother ♪</i>

438
00:23:59,375 --> 00:24:02,208
<i>♪ I always wanted a brother
just like you ♪</i>

439
00:24:03,208 --> 00:24:05,040
[both] <i>♪ And I always wanted
a brother ♪</i>

440
00:24:05,208 --> 00:24:06,915
<i>♪ I always wanted a brother ♪</i>

441
00:24:07,083 --> 00:24:10,208
<i>♪ I always wanted a brother
just like you ♪</i>

442
00:24:10,375 --> 00:24:11,415
[Mufasa] <i>♪ You see
that tree? ♪</i>

443
00:24:12,208 --> 00:24:15,375
<i>♪ Those birds are watching
the world unfold ♪</i>

444
00:24:15,540 --> 00:24:17,708
<i>♪ The world unfold ♪</i>

445
00:24:17,875 --> 00:24:19,915
<i>- ♪ Oh, brother ♪
- ♪ My brother ♪</i>

446
00:24:20,083 --> 00:24:22,790
[Taka] <i>♪ When I'm king,
they will do as they're told ♪</i>

447
00:24:23,040 --> 00:24:25,665
<i>♪ You may look down on them ♪</i>

448
00:24:25,833 --> 00:24:27,500
<i>- ♪ But they are free ♪
- ♪ You can't catch me ♪</i>

449
00:24:27,665 --> 00:24:30,583
<i>♪ And where they go
cannot be controlled ♪</i>

450
00:24:30,750 --> 00:24:33,375
<i>♪ No one looks down on me ♪</i>

451
00:24:33,540 --> 00:24:35,625
<i>♪ They look down on us,
brother ♪</i>

452
00:24:36,250 --> 00:24:38,290
<i>♪ Some things you chase
but you cannot hold ♪</i>

453
00:24:38,458 --> 00:24:40,707
<i>♪ Okay, it's getting old,
let's go ♪</i>

454
00:24:40,708 --> 00:24:41,790
<i>♪ Let's go ♪</i>

455
00:24:41,958 --> 00:24:44,957
<i>♪ Hey, did your mama say ♪</i>

456
00:24:44,958 --> 00:24:46,875
<i>♪ That you could
learn this way? ♪</i>

457
00:24:47,165 --> 00:24:48,665
<i>♪ I've got to find a way,
find our prey ♪</i>

458
00:24:48,833 --> 00:24:50,000
<i>- ♪ Fine, I'll wait ♪</i>
- [both] <i>♪ Let's go ♪</i>

459
00:24:50,165 --> 00:24:52,665
- [chorus] <i>♪ Hey ♪
- ♪ I heard his father say ♪</i>

460
00:24:52,833 --> 00:24:54,833
<i>♪ He doesn't want this stray ♪</i>

461
00:24:55,415 --> 00:24:57,375
<i>♪ I dare you to say
that again to my face ♪</i>

462
00:24:57,540 --> 00:24:59,125
<i>♪ What did you say
'bout my brother? ♪</i>

463
00:24:59,290 --> 00:25:00,958
<i>♪ That's not a stray,
that's my brother ♪</i>

464
00:25:01,125 --> 00:25:04,583
<i>♪ You stay away from my
brother 'cause I say so ♪</i>

465
00:25:05,083 --> 00:25:06,875
<i>♪ If you put your paws
on my brother ♪</i>

466
00:25:07,083 --> 00:25:08,790
<i>♪ You'll meet the jaws
of his brother ♪</i>

467
00:25:08,958 --> 00:25:11,040
<i>♪ Those are the laws
for my brother ♪</i>

468
00:25:11,375 --> 00:25:12,914
<i>♪ Where'd he go? ♪</i>

469
00:25:12,915 --> 00:25:15,000
[♪ emotional music playing]

470
00:25:20,625 --> 00:25:24,333
<i>♪ I always wanted a brother ♪</i>

471
00:25:24,500 --> 00:25:28,290
<i>♪ I still remember my mother ♪</i>

472
00:25:28,458 --> 00:25:32,125
<i>♪ One season after another ♪</i>

473
00:25:32,290 --> 00:25:36,125
[chorus] <i>♪ One season
after another ♪</i>

474
00:25:36,290 --> 00:25:39,915
<i>♪ One season after another ♪</i>

475
00:25:40,540 --> 00:25:43,749
<i>♪ One season after another ♪</i>

476
00:25:43,750 --> 00:25:44,832
<i>♪ Everyone sing
for my brother ♪</i>

477
00:25:44,833 --> 00:25:46,374
<i>- ♪ Hey ♪
- ♪ I'd do anything ♪</i>

478
00:25:46,375 --> 00:25:47,583
<i>- ♪ For my brother ♪
- ♪ Hey ♪</i>

479
00:25:47,750 --> 00:25:48,749
<i>♪ Soon I'll be king
with my brother ♪</i>

480
00:25:48,750 --> 00:25:49,832
<i>♪ Hey ♪</i>

481
00:25:49,833 --> 00:25:51,500
<i>- ♪ By my side ♪
- ♪ Hey ♪</i>

482
00:25:51,665 --> 00:25:53,458
<i>- ♪ I always wanted a brother ♪
- ♪ Hey ♪</i>

483
00:25:53,625 --> 00:25:55,250
<i>- ♪ Now we rely on each other ♪
- ♪ Hey ♪</i>

484
00:25:55,415 --> 00:25:57,500
<i>- ♪ One season after another ♪
- ♪ Hey ♪</i>

485
00:25:57,833 --> 00:25:59,832
<i>- ♪ Hey, Mufasa ♪
- ♪ Yes, Taka? ♪</i>

486
00:25:59,833 --> 00:26:00,914
<i>♪ I'll race you
to the other side ♪</i>

487
00:26:00,915 --> 00:26:02,457
<i>- ♪ Hey ♪</i>
- [Mufasa] <i>♪ Race you ♪</i>

488
00:26:02,458 --> 00:26:03,914
<i>- ♪ To the other side ♪
- ♪ Hey ♪</i>

489
00:26:03,915 --> 00:26:06,375
<i>♪ Race you to the other side
Ha! ♪</i>

490
00:26:14,250 --> 00:26:15,708
Elephant stampede!

491
00:26:15,875 --> 00:26:17,457
Run for your lives!

492
00:26:17,458 --> 00:26:19,583
[all exclaiming, clamoring]

493
00:26:21,750 --> 00:26:22,833
[growling]

494
00:26:24,833 --> 00:26:26,083
[Taka laughing]

495
00:26:27,083 --> 00:26:29,290
[Mufasa] Chigaru jumped,
like, 20 feet.

496
00:26:29,458 --> 00:26:30,625
Oh, that's a new record.

497
00:26:30,790 --> 00:26:32,915
[Chigaru] Obasi,
they did it again.

498
00:26:33,083 --> 00:26:34,915
Your sons are nothing
but trouble.

499
00:26:35,083 --> 00:26:37,083
That one is not my son.

500
00:26:37,250 --> 00:26:39,165
They're heathens,
the both of them.

501
00:26:39,333 --> 00:26:42,540
This stray is forbidden
to be near the Shade Tree.

502
00:26:42,708 --> 00:26:43,958
Mufasa and I were just playing.

503
00:26:44,125 --> 00:26:46,625
You two will never be brothers.

504
00:26:46,790 --> 00:26:48,165
Now go back to the females

505
00:26:48,333 --> 00:26:51,040
and stay away from my son.

506
00:26:52,583 --> 00:26:55,000
Oh, your mother,
she adopts every lizard,

507
00:26:55,165 --> 00:26:57,500
speaks to passing grasshoppers.

508
00:26:57,665 --> 00:26:58,665
I want to go with him.

509
00:26:58,833 --> 00:27:00,458
You want to be with the females?

510
00:27:00,625 --> 00:27:02,208
You belong with the males.

511
00:27:02,375 --> 00:27:04,165
He gets to hunt with Mother.

512
00:27:04,458 --> 00:27:06,915
One day, he will betray you.

513
00:27:07,915 --> 00:27:09,665
That is what strays do.

514
00:27:09,833 --> 00:27:11,250
Mufasa would never betray me.

515
00:27:11,415 --> 00:27:12,708
[Obasi] Hey, hey.

516
00:27:12,875 --> 00:27:15,625
This will all be yours, my son.

517
00:27:15,790 --> 00:27:18,125
You will be king.

518
00:27:18,290 --> 00:27:19,540
So pay attention.

519
00:27:20,415 --> 00:27:23,083
Study every move I make.

520
00:27:24,250 --> 00:27:26,083
Sleeping again.

521
00:27:26,250 --> 00:27:27,333
That is what males do.

522
00:27:27,500 --> 00:27:30,665
We protect the pride as we nap.

523
00:27:30,833 --> 00:27:32,083
That's...

524
00:27:32,250 --> 00:27:34,040
Well, that's power.

525
00:27:37,875 --> 00:27:39,375
Power?

526
00:27:54,415 --> 00:27:55,583
Why are we stopping?

527
00:27:55,750 --> 00:27:57,415
Close your eyes.

528
00:27:57,915 --> 00:27:59,875
And tell me what you hear.

529
00:28:00,708 --> 00:28:02,750
What you feel.

530
00:28:07,540 --> 00:28:10,083
[Mufasa] There's
a herd of antelope

531
00:28:10,290 --> 00:28:12,665
heading across the dry lakebed.

532
00:28:12,833 --> 00:28:15,540
About half a day from here?

533
00:28:15,750 --> 00:28:17,790
[Eshe] And how do you know
they're not gazelles?

534
00:28:18,958 --> 00:28:21,040
[Mufasa] Their steps
are too heavy.

535
00:28:21,250 --> 00:28:23,540
- Moving way too slow.
- [Eshe] What else?

536
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:26,125
Come on. You can do it.

537
00:28:26,290 --> 00:28:32,000
[Mufasa sighs] When the wind
hits their horns, it moves up

538
00:28:32,165 --> 00:28:36,040
instead of across.
So, definitely antelope horns.

539
00:28:36,208 --> 00:28:37,708
[Eshe] Very good.

540
00:28:39,208 --> 00:28:40,415
[grunts]

541
00:28:43,790 --> 00:28:46,125
What is it, Mufasa?
What's wrong?

542
00:28:46,290 --> 00:28:48,125
Sometimes I get a scent.

543
00:28:48,290 --> 00:28:50,665
It's barely a trace on the wind.

544
00:28:50,833 --> 00:28:52,415
And it smells like home.

545
00:28:57,000 --> 00:28:58,000
Then it's gone.

546
00:28:58,250 --> 00:29:00,958
Mufasa, your parents
are still out there.

547
00:29:01,125 --> 00:29:02,165
We can keep looking.

548
00:29:02,333 --> 00:29:03,540
I lost them, Eshe.

549
00:29:03,708 --> 00:29:05,833
You're wasting your time
training me like this.

550
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:08,875
But these skills you have,
no other male has them.

551
00:29:09,040 --> 00:29:11,250
Obasi will never accept me.

552
00:29:11,415 --> 00:29:13,915
I'll never be his blood.
His family.

553
00:29:14,083 --> 00:29:15,290
But you are my family.

554
00:29:15,458 --> 00:29:18,540
And if Obasi could see
how gifted you are...

555
00:29:18,708 --> 00:29:21,583
Well, maybe I like being
a stray, you know. [chuckles]

556
00:29:21,750 --> 00:29:24,290
No rules, no responsibility.

557
00:29:24,458 --> 00:29:25,958
[stutters] I'm the lucky one,
Eshe.

558
00:29:26,125 --> 00:29:27,500
What do you mean, Mufasa?

559
00:29:27,665 --> 00:29:29,665
I never have to be like Taka.

560
00:29:30,540 --> 00:29:32,290
I never have to be king.

561
00:29:41,708 --> 00:29:42,790
[growls]

562
00:29:45,458 --> 00:29:47,625
Did he say, "no rules
and no responsibility"?

563
00:29:47,790 --> 00:29:50,125
An outcast, afraid of water,
never takes a bath.

564
00:29:50,290 --> 00:29:51,665
Which means he smells like me.

565
00:29:51,833 --> 00:29:53,083
Which is not good.

566
00:29:53,250 --> 00:29:56,125
Well, either way, I think that
means that he's one of us.

567
00:29:56,250 --> 00:29:58,000
- [gasps] This is it.
- It's our time!

568
00:29:58,165 --> 00:29:59,164
This is our moment.

569
00:29:59,165 --> 00:30:01,290
And a-one,
and a-two and a-one, two...

570
00:30:01,458 --> 00:30:03,333
<i>♪ Hakuna Mufasa ♪</i>

571
00:30:03,500 --> 00:30:05,708
<i>♪ What a wonderful name ♪</i>

572
00:30:06,125 --> 00:30:07,750
<i>♪ Hakuna Mufasa ♪</i>

573
00:30:07,915 --> 00:30:10,165
<i>♪ He ain't no passin' craze ♪</i>

574
00:30:10,333 --> 00:30:11,415
<i>♪ It means no... ♪</i>

575
00:30:11,583 --> 00:30:12,750
- Stop!
- What?

576
00:30:12,915 --> 00:30:14,165
Don't go there.

577
00:30:14,333 --> 00:30:15,749
All right, all right,
Rafiki's right.

578
00:30:15,750 --> 00:30:16,833
We'll get letters from legal.

579
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:18,708
Those vultures will take
everything we have.

580
00:30:18,875 --> 00:30:20,625
Which, technically, is nothing.

581
00:30:20,790 --> 00:30:22,000
Look at us.
We're naked animals.

582
00:30:22,165 --> 00:30:23,458
No wonder I'm always freezing.

583
00:30:23,625 --> 00:30:24,624
They want this!

584
00:30:24,625 --> 00:30:25,708
- [Timon] Come on, Pumbaa.
- [sighs]

585
00:30:25,833 --> 00:30:26,833
Let's bring it home.

586
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:28,290
<i>♪ Hakuna Mufasa ♪</i>

587
00:30:28,458 --> 00:30:29,458
Quiet!

588
00:30:29,915 --> 00:30:31,833
Kiara's a music snob.

589
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:33,915
Rafiki, keep going.

590
00:30:36,165 --> 00:30:37,499
[Rafiki] <i>Later that day,</i>

591
00:30:37,500 --> 00:30:41,375
<i>Eshe was teaching Mufasa
how to hunt in pairs.</i>

592
00:30:41,625 --> 00:30:45,540
<i>But, as Taka was
secretly watching,</i>

593
00:30:45,708 --> 00:30:48,125
<i>something terrible
was hunting them.</i>

594
00:30:48,915 --> 00:30:50,458
[growling]

595
00:30:53,540 --> 00:30:55,750
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

596
00:31:11,083 --> 00:31:12,290
[sniffs]

597
00:31:15,915 --> 00:31:17,083
[growling]

598
00:31:35,708 --> 00:31:37,040
[growling]

599
00:31:38,750 --> 00:31:40,040
[bleating]

600
00:31:43,540 --> 00:31:44,625
Mufasa, run!

601
00:31:44,958 --> 00:31:46,083
[roaring]

602
00:31:46,958 --> 00:31:48,000
Eshe!

603
00:31:48,790 --> 00:31:49,790
Mother.

604
00:31:51,040 --> 00:31:52,040
Mother!

605
00:31:53,250 --> 00:31:54,250
Eshe!

606
00:31:56,540 --> 00:31:57,958
[roaring]

607
00:32:05,250 --> 00:32:06,665
[panting]

608
00:32:10,208 --> 00:32:11,375
[Eshe] Keep moving, Mufasa.

609
00:32:12,500 --> 00:32:14,165
They go for the neck!

610
00:32:15,750 --> 00:32:16,750
[growls]

611
00:32:22,540 --> 00:32:24,875
[both growling]

612
00:32:28,040 --> 00:32:29,415
[roaring]

613
00:32:32,540 --> 00:32:34,000
[Eshe] It's okay, Mufasa.

614
00:32:34,790 --> 00:32:37,250
- It's okay.
- [panting]

615
00:32:37,375 --> 00:32:38,833
It's okay.

616
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:41,500
That was very brave of you,
Mufasa.

617
00:32:41,665 --> 00:32:42,665
Thank you.

618
00:32:50,040 --> 00:32:51,290
Eshe...

619
00:32:51,458 --> 00:32:52,833
What has happened?

620
00:32:53,833 --> 00:32:56,290
[stutters] Are you hurt?

621
00:32:57,500 --> 00:33:00,458
They were huge.
White as ghosts.

622
00:33:00,625 --> 00:33:02,125
Like nothing I've seen before.

623
00:33:04,375 --> 00:33:05,790
Oh, Obasi.

624
00:33:07,040 --> 00:33:09,625
Had Mufasa not been there, I...

625
00:33:09,750 --> 00:33:11,000
[growls]

626
00:33:14,583 --> 00:33:15,583
Taka.

627
00:33:25,290 --> 00:33:29,290
I owe you a great debt, Mufasa.

628
00:33:29,458 --> 00:33:31,790
[growls] We need to prepare.

629
00:33:31,958 --> 00:33:34,540
They're downwind
less than a day away.

630
00:33:35,833 --> 00:33:36,833
No.

631
00:33:37,375 --> 00:33:38,875
You couldn't possibly know this.

632
00:33:39,040 --> 00:33:41,290
Send a scout and you'll see...

633
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:43,708
they'll be coming for us.

634
00:33:44,915 --> 00:33:45,915
Chigaru.

635
00:33:48,208 --> 00:33:50,458
Father, please, let me explain.

636
00:33:50,625 --> 00:33:52,458
No. Not now.

637
00:33:54,540 --> 00:33:55,958
Taka, come.

638
00:34:07,458 --> 00:34:09,458
[♪ ominous music playing]

639
00:34:16,583 --> 00:34:18,208
Where is my son?

640
00:34:18,375 --> 00:34:20,291
There was a young lion, Majesty.

641
00:34:20,458 --> 00:34:21,666
He fought Shaju.

642
00:34:22,750 --> 00:34:25,833
And yet you came back.

643
00:34:27,125 --> 00:34:28,833
You survived.

644
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:32,083
I was badly hurt. I promise,
Majesty. This is the truth.

645
00:34:32,250 --> 00:34:34,456
- The truth?
- Yes, the truth.

646
00:34:34,458 --> 00:34:35,833
[scoffs]

647
00:34:36,000 --> 00:34:37,914
The truth is standing
behind you.

648
00:34:37,916 --> 00:34:39,208
[growling]

649
00:34:42,375 --> 00:34:44,666
- There were others, Majesty.
- No, no, no.

650
00:34:44,833 --> 00:34:46,625
But only one left blood
on his mane.

651
00:34:46,791 --> 00:34:49,208
[lioness] Which means
he left Shaju to die.

652
00:34:49,375 --> 00:34:50,666
Saved himself.

653
00:34:50,833 --> 00:34:53,708
This young lion,
was he their king?

654
00:34:53,875 --> 00:34:55,333
His blood is common. Ordinary.

655
00:34:55,500 --> 00:34:56,500
[lion roars] Answer me!

656
00:34:57,083 --> 00:34:59,708
Was he their king?

657
00:34:59,875 --> 00:35:04,375
No, Kiros,
you are the only king.

658
00:35:04,541 --> 00:35:07,583
[grunts] An ordinary lion?

659
00:35:07,750 --> 00:35:10,583
And you left my son to die?

660
00:35:10,750 --> 00:35:12,625
[stuttering] I was injured.
There was no choice.

661
00:35:12,791 --> 00:35:14,833
Please, Majesty,
you have to believe me.

662
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:17,083
There's no reason to fear me.

663
00:35:17,250 --> 00:35:19,708
I would never harm
one of my own.

664
00:35:20,250 --> 00:35:22,000
Thank you, Majesty.

665
00:35:22,833 --> 00:35:24,750
I'll leave that pleasure

666
00:35:24,916 --> 00:35:25,916
to them.

667
00:35:27,583 --> 00:35:29,541
Majesty! No. Kiros!

668
00:35:30,333 --> 00:35:31,333
Kiros!

669
00:35:35,750 --> 00:35:36,916
[gasps]

670
00:35:41,500 --> 00:35:43,456
[Obasi] <i>No one
can ever know you ran.</i>

671
00:35:43,458 --> 00:35:45,250
<i>That you ran from your mother.</i>

672
00:35:46,125 --> 00:35:48,458
It never happened, Taka.
Do you understand?

673
00:35:48,625 --> 00:35:50,708
But I didn't know. I was
just... I was just scared.

674
00:35:51,208 --> 00:35:54,833
It doesn't matter.
We must protect the bloodline.

675
00:35:55,000 --> 00:35:58,083
Protect it with a lie?
Father, that's deceitful.

676
00:35:58,250 --> 00:36:02,416
Deceit is a tool
of a great king.

677
00:36:03,958 --> 00:36:04,958
Taka...

678
00:36:05,875 --> 00:36:08,875
it's what kings must do.

679
00:36:09,041 --> 00:36:10,666
But I'm not a king.

680
00:36:11,041 --> 00:36:12,416
I'm just your son.

681
00:36:12,875 --> 00:36:13,875
[Chigaru] Obasi!

682
00:36:14,875 --> 00:36:16,125
Chigaru.

683
00:36:16,291 --> 00:36:17,291
Obasi!

684
00:36:17,875 --> 00:36:21,625
Chigaru, I'm here.
What did you see?

685
00:36:21,791 --> 00:36:23,291
They're coming this way, Obasi.

686
00:36:23,458 --> 00:36:25,375
Two lions for every one of ours.

687
00:36:25,541 --> 00:36:27,208
Each one bigger than the next,

688
00:36:27,375 --> 00:36:31,333
but none as mighty as Kiros,
their terrifying king.

689
00:36:31,833 --> 00:36:33,291
Outsiders.

690
00:36:33,833 --> 00:36:35,750
The stories were all true.

691
00:36:36,708 --> 00:36:39,000
I must protect
the bloodline, Eshe.

692
00:36:39,166 --> 00:36:41,041
The future of this pride.

693
00:36:41,583 --> 00:36:44,041
Taka, you are that future.

694
00:36:44,208 --> 00:36:46,041
Future? Dad, what do you mean?

695
00:36:46,875 --> 00:36:48,250
I'm sending you away.

696
00:36:49,166 --> 00:36:50,333
Far from here.

697
00:36:51,166 --> 00:36:55,291
You will leave and start a new
life, a new beginning.

698
00:36:55,500 --> 00:36:57,625
I need you to go with him,
Mufasa,

699
00:36:57,791 --> 00:36:59,416
to pledge your loyalty.

700
00:37:00,208 --> 00:37:01,958
They'll arrive with the sunrise.

701
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:12,083
Where will we go, Eshe?

702
00:37:12,250 --> 00:37:13,708
Without you, I have no home.

703
00:37:13,875 --> 00:37:16,958
Mufasa, you and Taka together.
That...

704
00:37:17,916 --> 00:37:19,000
- That is home.
- Eshe...

705
00:37:19,166 --> 00:37:20,833
Mufasa, look out there.

706
00:37:21,458 --> 00:37:22,583
Beyond the light...

707
00:37:22,750 --> 00:37:24,041
You know what I see?

708
00:37:24,208 --> 00:37:26,581
I see the place your mother
told you about,

709
00:37:26,583 --> 00:37:28,833
a place beyond the river's end.

710
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:30,748
Across the deepest canyon

711
00:37:30,750 --> 00:37:32,291
on the other side
of the mountains,

712
00:37:32,458 --> 00:37:34,875
a place beyond
the horizon itself.

713
00:37:35,625 --> 00:37:37,208
A pride land so green,

714
00:37:37,750 --> 00:37:40,208
so perfect

715
00:37:40,708 --> 00:37:43,416
that to see it is to see

716
00:37:43,583 --> 00:37:44,750
<i>Milele.</i>

717
00:37:44,916 --> 00:37:47,500
[softly] Yes. Forever.

718
00:37:47,666 --> 00:37:49,539
My parents spoke
of <i>Milele</i> often.

719
00:37:49,541 --> 00:37:51,750
My mother told me
it was where we were going.

720
00:37:51,916 --> 00:37:53,416
And don't you see, Mufasa?

721
00:37:53,583 --> 00:37:54,708
You must keep going.

722
00:37:54,875 --> 00:37:57,125
You must continue your journey
toward the light.

723
00:37:57,291 --> 00:38:00,125
Please, Eshe.
I can't lose you.

724
00:38:00,291 --> 00:38:02,916
You have my love always, Mufasa.

725
00:38:03,083 --> 00:38:05,958
But your family is still out
there, waiting for you.

726
00:38:06,125 --> 00:38:07,666
I can feel their presence.

727
00:38:07,833 --> 00:38:09,500
And I know you can, too.

728
00:38:10,500 --> 00:38:11,500
Go.

729
00:38:12,125 --> 00:38:15,250
Go, Mufasa.
Find your way home.

730
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:26,750
Mother, please forgive me.
I beg you.

731
00:38:26,916 --> 00:38:29,125
There's no need, my love.

732
00:38:29,291 --> 00:38:32,166
Taka, your moment of courage
will come.

733
00:38:40,750 --> 00:38:42,250
Now both of you go.

734
00:38:43,250 --> 00:38:45,250
Go and find your place

735
00:38:45,666 --> 00:38:47,250
in the Circle of Life.

736
00:38:48,583 --> 00:38:50,583
[♪ valiant music playing]

737
00:39:05,083 --> 00:39:08,000
They left their family
never to see them again?

738
00:39:08,166 --> 00:39:09,333
- [Timon whimpers]
- This story is killing me.

739
00:39:09,500 --> 00:39:11,041
It's toying with my emotions.

740
00:39:11,208 --> 00:39:12,666
[Pumbaa] And here
is the worst part.

741
00:39:13,083 --> 00:39:14,541
- What's that?
- I'm out of crickets.

742
00:39:14,708 --> 00:39:15,958
Oh, maybe that's for the best.

743
00:39:16,125 --> 00:39:17,666
I need a bathroom break
before the second act.

744
00:39:17,833 --> 00:39:19,291
Everyone wait for me.

745
00:39:24,541 --> 00:39:25,541
I am back.

746
00:39:25,708 --> 00:39:26,914
Pumbaa, did you wash
your hooves?

747
00:39:26,916 --> 00:39:27,998
[Pumbaa] Mm-hmm.

748
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:29,250
- Pumbaa?
- I did. I did.

749
00:39:29,416 --> 00:39:30,666
- [Timon] Pumbaa?
- I'm just gonna walk

750
00:39:30,833 --> 00:39:32,416
- on them again right after.
- Pumbaa?

751
00:39:32,583 --> 00:39:33,750
[groans]

752
00:39:34,583 --> 00:39:37,000
Rafiki, did the Outsiders come?

753
00:39:37,166 --> 00:39:38,166
[Rafiki] Yes.

754
00:39:38,333 --> 00:39:41,083
And as the hunters led Kiros
into the Valley of Kings,

755
00:39:41,333 --> 00:39:44,625
<i>Obasi and Eshe
stood their ground.</i>

756
00:39:45,625 --> 00:39:47,625
[♪ tense music playing]

757
00:39:54,666 --> 00:39:55,916
[growling]

758
00:39:57,250 --> 00:40:00,416
Which one of you is king?

759
00:40:00,583 --> 00:40:03,541
You have no reason
to challenge me.

760
00:40:03,708 --> 00:40:08,208
[chuckles] Does this look
like a challenge, King?

761
00:40:08,458 --> 00:40:11,041
There are rules among lions.

762
00:40:11,208 --> 00:40:12,375
Not anymore.

763
00:40:13,208 --> 00:40:16,041
While you ruled this pride,
I've built my army.

764
00:40:16,708 --> 00:40:18,041
Yours is the last pride

765
00:40:18,208 --> 00:40:21,166
in the Valley of Kings,
which means

766
00:40:21,333 --> 00:40:25,208
everything the light touches
belongs to me.

767
00:40:25,375 --> 00:40:27,041
There will be one ruler.

768
00:40:27,208 --> 00:40:29,833
One Lion King.

769
00:40:29,958 --> 00:40:31,708
[lions growling]

770
00:40:35,750 --> 00:40:37,789
<i>♪ You say you're the king ♪</i>

771
00:40:37,791 --> 00:40:41,041
<i>♪ But you lie around
in the shade ♪</i>

772
00:40:41,208 --> 00:40:43,666
<i>♪ Out of shape, unafraid ♪</i>

773
00:40:44,791 --> 00:40:48,041
<i>♪ The moon cuts a path
through the sky ♪</i>

774
00:40:48,208 --> 00:40:50,291
<i>♪ By night or by day ♪</i>

775
00:40:50,500 --> 00:40:52,666
<i>♪ It doesn't obey ♪</i>

776
00:40:52,833 --> 00:40:55,041
<i>♪ And neither do I ♪</i>

777
00:40:55,208 --> 00:40:57,706
<i>♪ You took my son ♪</i>

778
00:40:57,708 --> 00:40:58,791
[growls]

779
00:40:59,541 --> 00:41:02,291
<i>♪ I hope you can run ♪</i>

780
00:41:02,833 --> 00:41:06,541
<i>♪ 'Cause I'm going to be
the last thing you see ♪</i>

781
00:41:06,708 --> 00:41:08,625
<i>♪ Before you go bye-bye ♪</i>

782
00:41:09,125 --> 00:41:11,041
<i>♪ There you go, bye-bye ♪</i>

783
00:41:12,250 --> 00:41:15,666
<i>♪ Climb every tree
Cross land and sea ♪</i>

784
00:41:15,833 --> 00:41:17,541
<i>♪ I'll make you go bye-bye ♪</i>

785
00:41:17,958 --> 00:41:19,875
<i>♪ I'll make you go bye-bye ♪</i>

786
00:41:20,916 --> 00:41:23,248
<i>♪ Everything
in my clutches, ha! ♪</i>

787
00:41:23,250 --> 00:41:24,666
<i>♪ Bye-bye ♪</i>

788
00:41:25,583 --> 00:41:28,041
<i>♪ Everything
the light touches ♪</i>

789
00:41:29,958 --> 00:41:32,958
<i>♪ The Circle of Life
is a lie ♪</i>

790
00:41:33,125 --> 00:41:34,875
<i>♪ A pretty way to say ♪</i>

791
00:41:35,041 --> 00:41:37,666
<i>♪ There are predators
and prey ♪</i>

792
00:41:38,625 --> 00:41:41,875
<i>♪ That circle of vultures
up high ♪</i>

793
00:41:42,041 --> 00:41:44,208
<i>♪ They keep stealing glances ♪</i>

794
00:41:44,375 --> 00:41:46,416
<i>♪ They don't like
your chances ♪</i>

795
00:41:46,583 --> 00:41:48,875
<i>♪ And neither do I ♪</i>

796
00:41:49,208 --> 00:41:52,250
<i>♪ I run my pride ♪</i>

797
00:41:53,583 --> 00:41:56,000
<i>♪ You run and hide ♪</i>

798
00:41:57,000 --> 00:42:00,500
<i>♪ 'Cause I'm going to be
the last thing you see ♪</i>

799
00:42:00,666 --> 00:42:02,500
<i>♪ Before you go bye-bye ♪</i>

800
00:42:02,916 --> 00:42:04,791
<i>♪ There you go, bye-bye ♪</i>

801
00:42:05,791 --> 00:42:09,500
<i>♪ Climb every tree
Cross land and sea ♪</i>

802
00:42:09,666 --> 00:42:11,708
<i>♪ Until you go bye-bye ♪</i>

803
00:42:11,875 --> 00:42:13,708
<i>♪ Will you go bye-bye? ♪</i>

804
00:42:14,750 --> 00:42:18,166
<i>♪ Bye-bye,
for vengeance is mine ♪</i>

805
00:42:19,083 --> 00:42:22,000
<i>♪ If I'm the last of my line ♪</i>

806
00:42:22,166 --> 00:42:27,958
<i>♪ I must be strong ♪</i>

807
00:42:28,125 --> 00:42:29,333
<i>♪ Gotta go bye-bye ♪</i>

808
00:42:29,791 --> 00:42:31,625
<i>♪ I'll make you go bye-bye ♪</i>

809
00:42:32,625 --> 00:42:33,875
[vocalizing]

810
00:42:36,958 --> 00:42:38,166
<i>♪ Bye-bye ♪</i>

811
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:48,541
We have to move.
They'll be tracking us.

812
00:42:49,083 --> 00:42:50,583
- Taka!
- [Taka] What if you're wrong?

813
00:42:51,000 --> 00:42:52,000
What if they're okay?

814
00:42:52,125 --> 00:42:54,416
They live in you now.

815
00:42:54,833 --> 00:42:56,416
Follow me, brother.

816
00:42:57,208 --> 00:42:58,458
We have to move...

817
00:42:59,375 --> 00:43:00,583
together.

818
00:43:05,041 --> 00:43:06,625
[birds screeching]

819
00:43:18,416 --> 00:43:20,416
[♪ mysterious music playing]

820
00:43:25,291 --> 00:43:26,791
Run, Mufasa.

821
00:43:27,708 --> 00:43:29,500
Run!

822
00:43:30,750 --> 00:43:31,750
Hunters.

823
00:43:31,916 --> 00:43:33,916
- [Taka] What's the plan?
- [Mufasa] Uh...

824
00:43:34,291 --> 00:43:36,541
Run! Very fast!

825
00:43:36,875 --> 00:43:38,125
[lions growling]

826
00:43:39,000 --> 00:43:41,000
[♪ dramatic music playing]

827
00:43:42,083 --> 00:43:43,541
This way!

828
00:43:55,041 --> 00:43:56,208
[grunting]

829
00:43:58,166 --> 00:43:59,416
Back to the trees.

830
00:43:59,583 --> 00:44:01,250
We're trapped.
We have to swim.

831
00:44:01,416 --> 00:44:02,833
No, we have to fight.

832
00:44:03,000 --> 00:44:04,458
If we fight, we die.

833
00:44:04,625 --> 00:44:06,000
But if we swim, we drown.

834
00:44:06,166 --> 00:44:08,250
Okay, I didn't want to do this,

835
00:44:08,416 --> 00:44:10,500
- but I command you to swim!
- You what?

836
00:44:10,666 --> 00:44:13,291
You pledged your loyalty.
I command you to swim.

837
00:44:13,458 --> 00:44:15,958
Taka, this is not the time
for jokes.

838
00:44:16,125 --> 00:44:18,791
- [antelope bleating]
- [♪ ominous music playing]

839
00:44:25,000 --> 00:44:26,291
[lions growling]

840
00:44:30,541 --> 00:44:33,083
Which one of you killed my son?

841
00:44:33,250 --> 00:44:34,831
I did.
This lion with me is nothing

842
00:44:34,833 --> 00:44:36,414
but a stray. Let him go.

843
00:44:36,416 --> 00:44:38,208
Kiros, the other is no stray.

844
00:44:38,375 --> 00:44:40,125
He holds the blood of the pride.

845
00:44:40,291 --> 00:44:41,500
[Kiros chuckles]

846
00:44:41,666 --> 00:44:44,208
The last blood
of the king? Hmm.

847
00:44:45,458 --> 00:44:48,206
Blood for blood.

848
00:44:48,208 --> 00:44:50,291
[♪ dramatic music playing]

849
00:45:04,666 --> 00:45:05,958
[Taka] They're coming!

850
00:45:06,583 --> 00:45:07,708
What do we do?

851
00:45:07,875 --> 00:45:09,166
We find the advantage?

852
00:45:09,333 --> 00:45:10,373
What advantage?

853
00:45:10,375 --> 00:45:12,916
We're on a rock
in the middle of the water!

854
00:45:13,750 --> 00:45:16,416
Taka, this is it.
We go for the king.

855
00:45:17,291 --> 00:45:18,541
[Kiros growling]

856
00:45:24,583 --> 00:45:25,914
- [roars]
- [growls softly]

857
00:45:25,916 --> 00:45:27,083
[Taka] Mufasa, I'm ready.

858
00:45:27,875 --> 00:45:29,416
Just one last thing.

859
00:45:29,583 --> 00:45:30,625
- What?
- Chin up!

860
00:45:31,625 --> 00:45:33,333
Taka!

861
00:45:33,583 --> 00:45:36,248
- [Mufasa screaming]
- [Taka] This was a bad idea.

862
00:45:36,250 --> 00:45:37,625
[screams]

863
00:45:42,083 --> 00:45:43,250
[gasping]

864
00:45:45,041 --> 00:45:46,373
- [Taka] Mufasa!
- [Mufasa exclaims]

865
00:45:46,375 --> 00:45:47,623
Mufasa!

866
00:45:47,625 --> 00:45:49,041
[both exclaiming]

867
00:45:49,916 --> 00:45:51,083
[coughs]

868
00:45:51,875 --> 00:45:53,041
[growls]

869
00:45:55,208 --> 00:45:56,414
- [chuckling] Mufasa...
- Yeah! [chuckles]

870
00:45:56,416 --> 00:45:57,498
- We're alive.
- Ah!

871
00:45:57,500 --> 00:45:59,791
I did it. I saved us.

872
00:46:01,541 --> 00:46:02,623
[gasps]

873
00:46:02,625 --> 00:46:04,083
You were saying?

874
00:46:07,875 --> 00:46:09,875
[♪ dramatic music playing]

875
00:46:14,375 --> 00:46:15,750
[gasping]

876
00:46:23,416 --> 00:46:24,541
[exclaims]

877
00:46:25,541 --> 00:46:26,875
[screams]

878
00:46:32,291 --> 00:46:34,333
[Taka] Okay. Okay.

879
00:46:34,500 --> 00:46:36,208
No... No more water.

880
00:46:36,375 --> 00:46:38,416
Tell me you can track them
down river.

881
00:46:38,583 --> 00:46:40,833
We can track them anywhere.

882
00:46:41,000 --> 00:46:43,583
They can run,
but they can't hide.

883
00:46:44,958 --> 00:46:47,291
So just to be clear,
we're not in this story?

884
00:46:47,458 --> 00:46:48,748
It feels a little bit like

885
00:46:48,750 --> 00:46:50,750
Kiros is stealing
my thunder here.

886
00:46:50,916 --> 00:46:52,916
Yeah. You know,
I don't feel seen.

887
00:46:53,166 --> 00:46:54,706
No. There's a lotta stories
with all of us.

888
00:46:54,708 --> 00:46:55,789
Tell one of those!

889
00:46:55,791 --> 00:46:57,625
Can I make one small suggestion?

890
00:46:57,791 --> 00:47:00,375
Less childhood trauma,
more meerkat.

891
00:47:00,541 --> 00:47:03,250
Rafiki, I know
who Taka's gonna be.

892
00:47:03,416 --> 00:47:06,000
Oh. Me too. It's so obvious.

893
00:47:06,166 --> 00:47:07,833
But maybe, just so we're on
the same page, tell me?

894
00:47:08,000 --> 00:47:09,708
- Is it Simba? Is it me?
- Pumbaa.

895
00:47:09,875 --> 00:47:11,666
- Oh, wait. Am I Obasi?
- [sighs]

896
00:47:11,833 --> 00:47:12,831
That makes no sense.

897
00:47:12,833 --> 00:47:14,041
But seriously,
I have one question.

898
00:47:15,708 --> 00:47:17,125
Am I Taka?

899
00:47:17,541 --> 00:47:20,875
[in sing-song voice] ♪ I did
it again, I did it again ♪

900
00:47:21,250 --> 00:47:24,914
Not that I'm counting,
but I saved your hide. Again!

901
00:47:24,916 --> 00:47:27,498
[chuckles] As much as
it kills you to say it,

902
00:47:27,500 --> 00:47:29,125
let's hear a little,
"Thank you, Taka."

903
00:47:29,291 --> 00:47:31,414
[chuckles] You want me
to thank you

904
00:47:31,416 --> 00:47:33,083
for pushing me off a waterfall?

905
00:47:33,250 --> 00:47:35,581
Yes, and you're welcome.
[scoffs]

906
00:47:35,583 --> 00:47:36,831
Look, it's not my fault

907
00:47:36,833 --> 00:47:38,248
crocodiles are simply
attracted to you.

908
00:47:38,250 --> 00:47:40,498
[laughing] Don't...
Don't say that.

909
00:47:40,500 --> 00:47:41,708
[Taka laughs]

910
00:47:43,708 --> 00:47:46,708
[in sing-song voice] ♪ I did
it again, I did it...

911
00:47:46,875 --> 00:47:48,123
[animal growls]

912
00:47:48,125 --> 00:47:49,416
- Mufasa.
- [Mufasa shushes]

913
00:47:50,041 --> 00:47:51,833
[stutters] Is it them?
Is it the Outsiders?

914
00:47:52,000 --> 00:47:53,875
[Mufasa] No.
She's right there.

915
00:47:54,041 --> 00:47:55,166
"She"?

916
00:47:55,333 --> 00:47:57,416
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

917
00:47:57,625 --> 00:47:59,291
There's no place to run.

918
00:47:59,458 --> 00:48:00,875
We have your scent.

919
00:48:01,166 --> 00:48:02,206
[lioness] My scent?

920
00:48:02,208 --> 00:48:04,708
[scoffs] I've been stalking
you two all night.

921
00:48:05,166 --> 00:48:06,708
[chuckles]
That's not possible.

922
00:48:06,875 --> 00:48:08,333
[lioness] Then
why did I circle you

923
00:48:08,500 --> 00:48:09,750
three times in this wood

924
00:48:09,916 --> 00:48:12,125
while you two were
chasing each other's tails?

925
00:48:28,333 --> 00:48:30,000
- [roars]
- [Taka exclaims]

926
00:48:31,625 --> 00:48:33,250
Uh... That's embarrassing.

927
00:48:33,791 --> 00:48:37,166
Yeah, well, I, uh,
meant to do that, so...

928
00:48:37,333 --> 00:48:39,250
Still think I'm afraid?

929
00:48:41,833 --> 00:48:42,998
[Mufasa] Why are you
following us?

930
00:48:43,000 --> 00:48:44,414
I was hoping to find my pride.

931
00:48:44,416 --> 00:48:45,498
What happened to them?

932
00:48:45,500 --> 00:48:46,583
[lioness] The Outsiders
happened.

933
00:48:47,041 --> 00:48:48,123
A few of us got away,

934
00:48:48,125 --> 00:48:50,833
but you're the only
other lions I've seen.

935
00:48:52,083 --> 00:48:53,083
You two better keep moving.

936
00:48:53,250 --> 00:48:54,500
Wait! Please.

937
00:48:54,666 --> 00:48:56,916
Um... My name is Taka.

938
00:48:58,083 --> 00:48:59,791
Son of Obasi.

939
00:48:59,958 --> 00:49:01,625
I know what it's like
to lose everything.

940
00:49:01,791 --> 00:49:03,041
Come with us. We can help you.

941
00:49:03,208 --> 00:49:04,791
I don't need any help.

942
00:49:04,958 --> 00:49:07,083
But you don't have anyone.

943
00:49:07,250 --> 00:49:09,875
She does indeed have someone.
Thank you very much.

944
00:49:10,041 --> 00:49:12,250
That's Zazu. Don't eat him.

945
00:49:12,416 --> 00:49:13,875
You heard her. Do not eat me.

946
00:49:14,041 --> 00:49:16,833
As a recent addition
to the King's Royal Guard,

947
00:49:17,000 --> 00:49:19,791
I must kindly ask you both
to move on.

948
00:49:19,958 --> 00:49:21,708
Thank you for stopping by.

949
00:49:21,875 --> 00:49:23,916
Your king hired a bird
to protect you?

950
00:49:24,208 --> 00:49:25,791
How high can you fly?

951
00:49:26,000 --> 00:49:28,625
- Mmm.
- Look, I needed a scout.

952
00:49:28,791 --> 00:49:30,375
Zazu was the last option.

953
00:49:30,541 --> 00:49:32,083
Well, next to last. [chuckles]

954
00:49:32,250 --> 00:49:34,083
Between Albert the Iguana and I,

955
00:49:34,250 --> 00:49:37,833
His Majesty decided
on the underling with wings.

956
00:49:38,000 --> 00:49:40,791
And thus, I became the
lead scout for the princess.

957
00:49:40,958 --> 00:49:42,498
It's my third day,
going swimmingly,

958
00:49:42,500 --> 00:49:43,750
if I may say so myself.

959
00:49:43,916 --> 00:49:45,208
Sarabi, you can say so as well.

960
00:49:45,375 --> 00:49:46,958
[Mufasa] How far do you think
you'll get with a bird?

961
00:49:47,125 --> 00:49:49,081
How far do you two geniuses
think you'll get

962
00:49:49,083 --> 00:49:51,000
stumbling around,
running into each other?

963
00:49:51,166 --> 00:49:53,083
All the way to <i>Milele.</i>

964
00:49:53,250 --> 00:49:55,041
<i>- Milele</i> is nothing but a myth.
- It's not a myth.

965
00:49:55,208 --> 00:49:57,289
Circle of Life
and fairy tale herds.

966
00:49:57,291 --> 00:49:58,373
- You're chasing something...
- Honestly.

967
00:49:58,375 --> 00:49:59,456
- ...that doesn't exist.
- As If.

968
00:49:59,458 --> 00:50:02,000
I don't know that <i>Milele</i>
exists, but right now,

969
00:50:02,166 --> 00:50:03,333
it's the only hope we have.

970
00:50:03,500 --> 00:50:06,333
We don't need hope.
We need food.

971
00:50:07,708 --> 00:50:09,956
[softly] Um...
Good job, brother.

972
00:50:09,958 --> 00:50:11,914
- Oh, real nice.
- [animal screeches]

973
00:50:11,916 --> 00:50:14,333
There's trouble in the trees.
My first real trouble,

974
00:50:14,500 --> 00:50:15,998
and I am going to pass.
Not going.

975
00:50:16,000 --> 00:50:17,500
I am staying right here,
thank you.

976
00:50:17,666 --> 00:50:20,875
Come on, Sarabi. Looks like
there's dinner headed our way.

977
00:50:21,416 --> 00:50:23,125
[stutters] Sarabi, if I may.

978
00:50:23,583 --> 00:50:26,375
He makes a valid point,
Your Highness.

979
00:50:26,666 --> 00:50:28,498
But, on the other hand,
he's a starving lion,

980
00:50:28,500 --> 00:50:30,458
he wants to eat me,
so I am slightly torn.

981
00:50:31,166 --> 00:50:32,458
[animals screeching]

982
00:50:33,750 --> 00:50:35,914
I think that went quite well,
all things considered.

983
00:50:35,916 --> 00:50:38,000
[♪ exhilarating music playing]

984
00:50:46,000 --> 00:50:49,500
[Rafiki] <i>And now, Kiara,
this is where I come in.</i>

985
00:50:58,500 --> 00:50:59,500
Rafiki.

986
00:51:00,041 --> 00:51:02,708
Order! We will have order
in the Congress of Baboons.

987
00:51:02,875 --> 00:51:04,873
Tonight, a cheetah
came into our trees

988
00:51:04,875 --> 00:51:06,333
for the third night in a row.

989
00:51:06,500 --> 00:51:07,833
Almost took one of our own.

990
00:51:08,000 --> 00:51:09,000
It was Rafiki's fault.

991
00:51:09,291 --> 00:51:11,250
He summoned the beast
with his dreams.

992
00:51:11,416 --> 00:51:12,664
[baboon 1] Rafiki
and his visions

993
00:51:12,666 --> 00:51:14,791
must be banished
once and for all.

994
00:51:14,958 --> 00:51:16,125
Rafiki tried to warn you.

995
00:51:16,291 --> 00:51:17,956
His dreams conjure our enemies.

996
00:51:17,958 --> 00:51:20,000
He talks to the spirits,
summons the devil.

997
00:51:20,166 --> 00:51:21,164
What are you talking about?

998
00:51:21,166 --> 00:51:22,291
[baboon 2] He's done it before.

999
00:51:22,458 --> 00:51:24,416
His brother was chased
from these very trees,

1000
00:51:24,583 --> 00:51:25,708
never to be seen again.

1001
00:51:25,875 --> 00:51:27,083
[female baboon]
Rafiki was just a child.

1002
00:51:27,250 --> 00:51:29,748
A child born with a leg that
does not work.

1003
00:51:29,750 --> 00:51:30,833
Yet somehow, he survived?

1004
00:51:31,000 --> 00:51:33,458
It was Rafiki who found water
in the dry season.

1005
00:51:33,625 --> 00:51:35,958
Who healed you, Inaki,
when you were sick.

1006
00:51:36,125 --> 00:51:39,208
He speaks to the insects,
converses with the moon.

1007
00:51:39,375 --> 00:51:40,831
Zala, you know what will happen

1008
00:51:40,833 --> 00:51:42,333
if you send him
down from the trees.

1009
00:51:42,500 --> 00:51:44,291
[Inaki] He is <i>amelaaniwa!</i>

1010
00:51:44,458 --> 00:51:45,458
A curse to us all.

1011
00:51:45,625 --> 00:51:46,623
[female baboon]
That's not true.

1012
00:51:46,625 --> 00:51:47,706
[baboon 2] He doesn't
belong here.

1013
00:51:47,708 --> 00:51:50,666
All in favor of banishment,
cover one eye.

1014
00:51:51,250 --> 00:51:52,416
[baboon 3] How can you
trust him?

1015
00:51:52,583 --> 00:51:54,375
[baboon 4] Don't trust him,
and I don't trust his magic!

1016
00:51:54,541 --> 00:51:55,541
[baboon 5] He doesn't
belong here.

1017
00:51:55,666 --> 00:51:57,416
[baboon 6] He's not a baboon.
And he never will be.

1018
00:51:57,583 --> 00:51:59,000
[baboon 7] He's not one of us.

1019
00:51:59,166 --> 00:52:01,125
- And so, it is time.
- [♪ solemn music playing]

1020
00:52:01,291 --> 00:52:02,583
[female baboon] No, wait.

1021
00:52:03,208 --> 00:52:04,625
Where will you go?

1022
00:52:04,791 --> 00:52:07,208
Where I should have gone
long ago.

1023
00:52:07,375 --> 00:52:09,416
To find all that was lost.

1024
00:52:10,083 --> 00:52:11,166
My family.

1025
00:52:11,333 --> 00:52:13,458
You can't survive on your own.

1026
00:52:13,625 --> 00:52:14,958
Nobody can.

1027
00:52:15,125 --> 00:52:17,500
And yet, here we are.

1028
00:52:19,458 --> 00:52:20,750
Oh, Rafiki.

1029
00:52:20,916 --> 00:52:25,375
The eye never forgets
what the heart has seen.

1030
00:52:31,958 --> 00:52:33,125
[grunts]

1031
00:52:38,750 --> 00:52:39,750
[sighs]

1032
00:52:45,708 --> 00:52:47,000
- [sighs]
- It's all right.

1033
00:52:57,041 --> 00:52:58,041
[growls]

1034
00:53:00,583 --> 00:53:01,708
[roars]

1035
00:53:03,208 --> 00:53:05,208
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

1036
00:53:07,333 --> 00:53:08,375
[grunts]

1037
00:53:12,000 --> 00:53:14,000
Hmm. <i>Jamaa.</i>

1038
00:53:15,333 --> 00:53:16,333
Hmm.

1039
00:53:20,750 --> 00:53:24,083
You can try to run, but I'm
afraid you won't get very far.

1040
00:53:24,250 --> 00:53:26,041
And why would I run from you?

1041
00:53:26,791 --> 00:53:28,750
Because we're lions.

1042
00:53:28,916 --> 00:53:31,625
As in... [roaring] lions!

1043
00:53:31,791 --> 00:53:34,248
[scoffs] A flea
can trouble a lion

1044
00:53:34,250 --> 00:53:36,125
more than a lion
can trouble a flea.

1045
00:53:36,291 --> 00:53:38,958
I don't think you understand
what's about to happen.

1046
00:53:39,125 --> 00:53:40,625
There's no place for you to go.

1047
00:53:40,791 --> 00:53:42,583
I am going forward.

1048
00:53:42,750 --> 00:53:44,166
I seriously doubt that.

1049
00:53:44,333 --> 00:53:48,125
It is easy to doubt everything
when you know nothing.

1050
00:53:48,291 --> 00:53:50,375
Can we get on with this, please?

1051
00:53:50,541 --> 00:53:53,833
If you take my life,
you will never find <i>Milele.</i>

1052
00:53:54,000 --> 00:53:55,750
Wait, did you say <i>Milele?</i>

1053
00:53:55,916 --> 00:53:58,750
That is where I'm going.
Toward the light.

1054
00:53:58,916 --> 00:54:02,541
I have been there many times
in my dreams.

1055
00:54:02,708 --> 00:54:04,708
My brother waits for me there.

1056
00:54:04,875 --> 00:54:06,208
I've seen the tree.

1057
00:54:06,375 --> 00:54:08,375
Can picture it. The two of us,

1058
00:54:08,541 --> 00:54:10,041
together again.

1059
00:54:10,208 --> 00:54:12,541
And why would anyone trust
a baboon's dream?

1060
00:54:12,708 --> 00:54:14,958
Sometimes, a dream
is all you have.

1061
00:54:15,125 --> 00:54:17,500
The only truth
that lives in you.

1062
00:54:17,666 --> 00:54:20,125
Like the memory of a great king.

1063
00:54:20,291 --> 00:54:21,708
How did you know?

1064
00:54:21,875 --> 00:54:25,166
Okay. Help us get to <i>Milele,</i>
and we will let you live.

1065
00:54:25,333 --> 00:54:26,916
- Do we have a deal?
- No.

1066
00:54:27,083 --> 00:54:28,250
What? Why?

1067
00:54:28,416 --> 00:54:31,416
Rafiki will let you live.

1068
00:54:31,583 --> 00:54:33,708
I've had enough of this!

1069
00:54:33,875 --> 00:54:35,541
Taka, do not eat him.

1070
00:54:35,708 --> 00:54:37,289
Wonderful.
Another misfit stray

1071
00:54:37,291 --> 00:54:38,666
we're not supposed to eat.

1072
00:54:38,833 --> 00:54:41,416
So, you expect us
to follow this baboon

1073
00:54:41,583 --> 00:54:44,541
to a place nobody
has ever seen? [scoffs]

1074
00:54:44,666 --> 00:54:47,166
- I'll be better off alone.
<i>- Hhe ntombazane.</i>

1075
00:54:47,333 --> 00:54:49,750
A single stick may smoke,

1076
00:54:49,916 --> 00:54:51,791
but it will never burn.

1077
00:54:55,000 --> 00:54:56,458
Okay, now that
there's five of us,

1078
00:54:56,625 --> 00:54:57,623
why don't we all go around

1079
00:54:57,625 --> 00:54:59,208
and say a fun fact
about ourselves?

1080
00:54:59,375 --> 00:55:00,375
I'll go first.

1081
00:55:00,541 --> 00:55:03,500
[chuckling] I once had
a crush on a flamingo.

1082
00:55:03,666 --> 00:55:05,666
[whispers] I've never
said that out loud.

1083
00:55:06,250 --> 00:55:07,291
And they're walking away.

1084
00:55:07,458 --> 00:55:09,250
Yeah, places to go,
kingdoms to see.

1085
00:55:09,416 --> 00:55:10,875
We're busy. Let's hustle.

1086
00:55:11,000 --> 00:55:13,000
[♪ exhilarating song playing
in other language]

1087
00:55:20,958 --> 00:55:23,416
Wait, wait, wait. Now you're
the star of this thing?

1088
00:55:23,583 --> 00:55:26,166
Someone's a little tired
of bein' second banana, huh?

1089
00:55:26,333 --> 00:55:28,625
All of a sudden, there's
a lotta Rafiki in this story.

1090
00:55:28,791 --> 00:55:30,664
You even gave yourself
a long-lost brother.

1091
00:55:30,666 --> 00:55:31,748
- Yeah.
- [Timon] What's next?

1092
00:55:31,750 --> 00:55:32,831
A funny catchphrase?

1093
00:55:32,833 --> 00:55:34,791
[Pumbaa] You gonna be fartin'
next? 'Cause that's my thing.

1094
00:55:34,958 --> 00:55:37,333
You cannot tell the story
of Mufasa

1095
00:55:37,500 --> 00:55:39,958
without the story of Rafiki.

1096
00:55:40,125 --> 00:55:41,498
[Timon] Oh, now he's even
talkin' about himself

1097
00:55:41,500 --> 00:55:42,581
in the third person.

1098
00:55:42,583 --> 00:55:43,916
Pretty soon, he'll have
his own fragrance.

1099
00:55:44,083 --> 00:55:46,458
[Pumbaa] And I'm the only one
with a fragrance around here.

1100
00:55:46,625 --> 00:55:48,166
It's called "Pumbaa by Pumbaa,"

1101
00:55:48,333 --> 00:55:50,833
and from what I hear,
it's pretty gross.

1102
00:55:51,458 --> 00:55:52,958
Mom? Dad?

1103
00:55:53,375 --> 00:55:55,750
If you can hear me, come home.

1104
00:55:56,708 --> 00:55:57,875
Please.

1105
00:55:58,291 --> 00:55:59,541
Come home.

1106
00:56:00,708 --> 00:56:03,000
- [♪ melancholic music playing]
- [thunder rumbling]

1107
00:56:07,291 --> 00:56:08,291
[Mufasa whispering] Mother?

1108
00:56:10,666 --> 00:56:11,666
Mother?

1109
00:56:15,708 --> 00:56:17,166
[voice echoes] <i>Milele.</i>

1110
00:56:17,500 --> 00:56:19,331
- Mother! [gasps]
- [grunts]

1111
00:56:19,333 --> 00:56:20,833
[breathing heavily]

1112
00:56:26,291 --> 00:56:27,375
[grunts softly]

1113
00:56:37,208 --> 00:56:38,833
- Rafiki.
- [Rafiki] <i>Ayi suka.</i>

1114
00:56:39,000 --> 00:56:40,666
- What are you doing?
- I am fishing.

1115
00:56:40,833 --> 00:56:43,291
[Mufasa] You're sitting on
a rock with your eyes closed.

1116
00:56:43,458 --> 00:56:46,708
My eyes are open.
It is my lids that are closed.

1117
00:56:46,875 --> 00:56:49,250
Why am I talking to a baboon?

1118
00:56:49,416 --> 00:56:53,166
I am not a baboon.
I am a mandrill.

1119
00:56:53,333 --> 00:56:56,041
No offense,
but a monkey is a monkey.

1120
00:56:56,208 --> 00:56:57,625
[Rafiki] And a stray is a stray.

1121
00:56:57,791 --> 00:56:58,791
What's that supposed to mean?

1122
00:56:58,916 --> 00:57:01,041
It means
we are very much the same.

1123
00:57:01,208 --> 00:57:02,541
<i>Siyafana.</i>

1124
00:57:02,708 --> 00:57:04,250
We are nothing alike.

1125
00:57:04,583 --> 00:57:07,750
Take a good look. I am a lion.

1126
00:57:07,916 --> 00:57:09,623
[Rafiki] A lion who fears water,

1127
00:57:09,625 --> 00:57:11,291
fears his own reflection.

1128
00:57:11,791 --> 00:57:13,498
Who can't sleep
because of what he sees

1129
00:57:13,500 --> 00:57:15,250
when he closes his eyes.

1130
00:57:15,416 --> 00:57:16,416
Huh?

1131
00:57:16,583 --> 00:57:19,458
You are afraid
of your dreams, Mufasa.

1132
00:57:19,625 --> 00:57:21,625
Afraid of what you see in them.

1133
00:57:21,791 --> 00:57:24,208
[Mufasa] I see my parents.

1134
00:57:24,916 --> 00:57:26,958
I feel them everywhere.

1135
00:57:27,125 --> 00:57:28,916
[Rafiki] Of course
you do, Mufasa.

1136
00:57:29,708 --> 00:57:32,125
You will feel them forever.

1137
00:57:32,541 --> 00:57:35,458
My mother, I hear her voice.

1138
00:57:35,916 --> 00:57:39,625
She tells me that we are
on a journey to <i>Milele,</i>

1139
00:57:39,833 --> 00:57:43,000
but I feel so lost without her.

1140
00:57:43,166 --> 00:57:46,625
Your journey
is not a dream, Mufasa.

1141
00:57:46,791 --> 00:57:48,583
Your mother is guiding you,

1142
00:57:48,875 --> 00:57:52,250
and where you are going,
a family awaits.

1143
00:57:52,958 --> 00:57:54,041
[grunts]

1144
00:57:55,333 --> 00:58:00,248
<i>Ah... Ni heshima
kukutana nawe, binamu.</i>

1145
00:58:00,250 --> 00:58:04,208
<i>Nenda kwa amani.
Ah...</i> [laughs]

1146
00:58:05,083 --> 00:58:06,250
[Mufasa] What are you doing?

1147
00:58:06,791 --> 00:58:07,791
We're starving.

1148
00:58:07,916 --> 00:58:09,333
'Twas not its time.

1149
00:58:09,583 --> 00:58:13,208
Instead, the fish has agreed
to let us share the water.

1150
00:58:14,833 --> 00:58:15,875
[sighs]

1151
00:58:17,000 --> 00:58:22,541
<i>Iketle Rafiki.
Iketle mosimane.</i>

1152
00:58:23,583 --> 00:58:24,708
I have a report.

1153
00:58:25,333 --> 00:58:26,458
It's morning.

1154
00:58:27,166 --> 00:58:28,791
End of report.

1155
00:58:29,875 --> 00:58:31,125
[grunts]

1156
00:58:36,541 --> 00:58:39,208
[Rafiki] The earth divided
is now a choice.

1157
00:58:39,416 --> 00:58:40,958
Around or down?

1158
00:58:41,125 --> 00:58:43,250
The decision is yours.

1159
00:58:46,125 --> 00:58:47,291
Mmm.

1160
00:58:47,416 --> 00:58:50,208
Look out there,
beyond the light.

1161
00:58:51,208 --> 00:58:53,791
Across the deepest canyon.

1162
00:58:55,166 --> 00:58:57,208
"Across the deepest canyon."

1163
00:58:57,916 --> 00:58:58,916
We should go down.

1164
00:58:59,083 --> 00:59:01,500
Why? Because of some
fairy tale? [scoffs]

1165
00:59:01,666 --> 00:59:03,041
The rocks will hide our tracks.

1166
00:59:03,208 --> 00:59:04,666
It's safer to go around.

1167
00:59:04,833 --> 00:59:06,250
I picked up their scents.

1168
00:59:06,416 --> 00:59:08,916
The only thing you picked up
is a hallucinating baboon.

1169
00:59:09,083 --> 00:59:10,166
I am a mandrill.

1170
00:59:10,333 --> 00:59:11,708
This is a waste of time.

1171
00:59:11,875 --> 00:59:13,291
Close your eyes.

1172
00:59:13,833 --> 00:59:14,833
What?

1173
00:59:15,000 --> 00:59:17,708
Tell me what you see.
What you feel.

1174
00:59:17,875 --> 00:59:19,250
There's nothing on the wind.

1175
00:59:19,416 --> 00:59:20,539
[Mufasa] No, they're moving

1176
00:59:20,541 --> 00:59:21,875
- through the bush willow.
- They, who?

1177
00:59:22,041 --> 00:59:24,875
The females, out front.
Come on.

1178
00:59:25,083 --> 00:59:27,125
Clear your thoughts.
Concentrate.

1179
00:59:27,291 --> 00:59:29,333
I am concentrating.

1180
00:59:41,083 --> 00:59:42,250
He's right.

1181
00:59:43,958 --> 00:59:45,291
We have to go down.

1182
00:59:45,583 --> 00:59:47,291
Wow. Wow, wow, wow.

1183
00:59:47,458 --> 00:59:49,416
<i>Ah! Uyabona mfana.</i>

1184
00:59:49,625 --> 00:59:52,708
Now the many sticks
will make fire as one.

1185
00:59:53,125 --> 00:59:55,791
Come on. We have places to go.

1186
00:59:55,958 --> 00:59:58,208
[Zazu] And kingdoms to see.

1187
00:59:58,375 --> 01:00:00,289
[Rafiki] And kingdoms to see!

1188
01:00:00,291 --> 01:00:03,250
- [laughs] <i>Masihambeni.</i>
- [♪ joyful music playing]

1189
01:00:03,541 --> 01:00:05,958
<i>♪ If you wanna go fast,
go alone ♪</i>

1190
01:00:06,958 --> 01:00:08,041
<i>♪ There's the road ♪</i>

1191
01:00:08,708 --> 01:00:10,083
<i>♪ Off you go ♪</i>

1192
01:00:10,291 --> 01:00:13,458
<i>♪ But if you wanna go far ♪</i>

1193
01:00:13,625 --> 01:00:15,333
<i>♪ We go together ♪</i>

1194
01:00:15,500 --> 01:00:17,291
<i>♪ So good, so far ♪</i>

1195
01:00:17,458 --> 01:00:19,125
<i>♪ We go together ♪</i>

1196
01:00:19,291 --> 01:00:21,748
<i>♪ Your father left you
in my care ♪</i>

1197
01:00:21,750 --> 01:00:23,081
[chorus vocalizing]

1198
01:00:23,083 --> 01:00:25,666
<i>♪ And now we're running
who knows where ♪</i>

1199
01:00:26,916 --> 01:00:29,125
<i>♪ Sometimes you need
a bird's-eye view ♪</i>

1200
01:00:29,291 --> 01:00:32,666
<i>♪ And I've got you
to see me through ♪</i>

1201
01:00:32,833 --> 01:00:34,333
<i>♪ By land, by air ♪</i>

1202
01:00:34,500 --> 01:00:36,416
<i>♪ If you wanna go fast,
go alone ♪</i>

1203
01:00:36,583 --> 01:00:37,581
<i>♪ Day and night ♪</i>

1204
01:00:37,583 --> 01:00:39,291
<i>- ♪ There's the road ♪
- ♪ I just might ♪</i>

1205
01:00:39,458 --> 01:00:41,458
<i>- ♪ Off you go ♪
- ♪ Yeah, right ♪</i>

1206
01:00:41,916 --> 01:00:44,125
[Rafiki and Sarabi]
<i>♪ If you wanna go far ♪</i>

1207
01:00:44,291 --> 01:00:46,041
[Rafiki, Sarabi and Zazu]
<i>♪ We go together ♪</i>

1208
01:00:46,208 --> 01:00:48,000
<i>♪ So good, so far ♪</i>

1209
01:00:48,166 --> 01:00:50,000
<i>♪ We go together ♪</i>

1210
01:00:50,666 --> 01:00:53,958
<i>♪ I will find
my family again ♪</i>

1211
01:00:54,375 --> 01:00:57,875
<i>♪ I will walk with you
until then ♪</i>

1212
01:00:58,208 --> 01:01:01,666
<i>♪ I will walk with you
till the end ♪</i>

1213
01:01:02,041 --> 01:01:05,083
<i>♪ It's much easier
with a friend ♪</i>

1214
01:01:05,916 --> 01:01:09,541
<i>♪ I will find
my family again ♪</i>

1215
01:01:09,708 --> 01:01:13,333
<i>♪ I will walk with you
until then ♪</i>

1216
01:01:13,500 --> 01:01:15,706
<i>♪ I will walk with you
till the end ♪</i>

1217
01:01:15,708 --> 01:01:16,791
[Zazu] <i>♪ Flying through ♪</i>

1218
01:01:17,458 --> 01:01:20,666
[Mufasa and Sarabi] <i>♪ It's
much easier with a friend ♪</i>

1219
01:01:20,833 --> 01:01:22,914
<i>♪ Like the clouds and rain ♪</i>

1220
01:01:22,916 --> 01:01:24,498
[chorus vocalizing]

1221
01:01:24,500 --> 01:01:27,583
<i>♪ Like a meal
in a field of grain ♪</i>

1222
01:01:28,458 --> 01:01:31,333
<i>♪ Like the flecks of gold
in your mane ♪</i>

1223
01:01:31,500 --> 01:01:35,791
<i>♪ Sarabi, you and me,
we go together ♪</i>

1224
01:01:35,958 --> 01:01:37,331
<i>♪ Like clouds and rain ♪</i>

1225
01:01:37,333 --> 01:01:39,708
[Mufasa and Sarabi] <i>♪ We will
find our family again ♪</i>

1226
01:01:39,875 --> 01:01:41,539
<i>♪ Like a meal
in a field of grain ♪</i>

1227
01:01:41,541 --> 01:01:43,708
[Mufasa and Sarabi] <i>♪ We will
walk together till then ♪</i>

1228
01:01:43,916 --> 01:01:46,373
<i>♪ Like the flecks of gold
in your mane, Sarabi ♪</i>

1229
01:01:46,375 --> 01:01:48,083
[Mufasa and Sarabi] <i>♪ We will
find our way to the end ♪</i>

1230
01:01:48,250 --> 01:01:49,748
<i>♪ You and me, we go together ♪</i>

1231
01:01:49,750 --> 01:01:51,208
[Mufasa and Sarabi] <i>♪ It's
much easier with a friend ♪</i>

1232
01:01:51,375 --> 01:01:53,498
[Rafiki] <i>♪ My brother waits
for me to find him ♪</i>

1233
01:01:53,500 --> 01:01:55,208
[Mufasa and Sarabi] <i>♪ We will
find our family again ♪</i>

1234
01:01:55,375 --> 01:01:57,539
<i>♪ My brother knows
I'm right behind him ♪</i>

1235
01:01:57,541 --> 01:01:59,041
[Mufasa and Sarabi] <i>♪ We will
walk together till then ♪</i>

1236
01:01:59,208 --> 01:02:00,664
<i>♪ My brother tends to lose
his way ♪</i>

1237
01:02:00,666 --> 01:02:01,791
[Mufasa and Sarabi] <i>♪ We will
find our way ♪</i>

1238
01:02:01,958 --> 01:02:03,375
<i>- ♪ And go astray, say ♪
- ♪ To the end ♪</i>

1239
01:02:03,541 --> 01:02:05,456
<i>♪ If you see my brother,
please remind him ♪</i>

1240
01:02:05,458 --> 01:02:07,248
[Mufasa and Sarabi] <i>♪ It's
much easier with a friend ♪</i>

1241
01:02:07,250 --> 01:02:08,914
- [chorus] <i>♪ Sondela ♪</i>
- [all] <i>♪ It's much easier ♪</i>

1242
01:02:08,916 --> 01:02:11,123
<i>- ♪ With a friend ♪
- ♪ Sondela mntanam! Sondela ♪</i>

1243
01:02:11,125 --> 01:02:14,331
- <i>♪ It's much easier ♪
- ♪ Sondela mntanam! Sondela ♪</i>

1244
01:02:14,333 --> 01:02:16,623
<i>♪ Sondela mntanam! Sondela ♪</i>

1245
01:02:16,625 --> 01:02:18,123
[Rafiki and Sarabi]
<i>♪ We won't go alone ♪</i>

1246
01:02:18,125 --> 01:02:19,208
- [lions] <i>♪ Not alone ♪</i>
- [vocalizing]

1247
01:02:19,333 --> 01:02:21,083
<i>- ♪ Here we go ♪
- ♪ Here we go ♪</i>

1248
01:02:21,250 --> 01:02:23,333
<i>- ♪ Down the road ♪
- ♪ Down the road ♪</i>

1249
01:02:23,541 --> 01:02:24,789
[Rafiki and Sarabi]
<i>♪ 'Cause we're gonna go far ♪</i>

1250
01:02:24,791 --> 01:02:25,875
- <i>♪ Hey, hey, hey, hey ♪
- ♪ Sondela ♪</i>

1251
01:02:26,041 --> 01:02:27,833
- <i>♪ We go together ♪
- ♪ Sondela mntanam! ♪</i>

1252
01:02:28,000 --> 01:02:29,791
<i>- ♪ So good, so far ♪
- ♪ Hey, hey, hey, hey ♪</i>

1253
01:02:29,958 --> 01:02:32,125
<i>- ♪ We go together ♪
- ♪ Uyayiqonda mntanam! ♪</i>

1254
01:02:33,791 --> 01:02:35,333
[all laughing]

1255
01:02:40,125 --> 01:02:42,541
[Rafiki] <i>As we headed
across the Great Valley,</i>

1256
01:02:43,166 --> 01:02:45,416
<i>the hunters tracked
our every move.</i>

1257
01:02:45,541 --> 01:02:46,833
[sniffing]

1258
01:02:47,791 --> 01:02:50,041
Kiros. They are not alone.

1259
01:02:50,208 --> 01:02:51,958
They've collected a lioness.

1260
01:02:52,125 --> 01:02:54,416
And a monkey.

1261
01:02:56,291 --> 01:02:57,583
[roars]

1262
01:03:04,416 --> 01:03:05,541
[Taka whispers] Mufasa.

1263
01:03:05,708 --> 01:03:07,623
[in normal voice] Mufasa.
You have to help me.

1264
01:03:07,625 --> 01:03:08,708
Help you how?

1265
01:03:08,833 --> 01:03:10,166
It's Sarabi, Mufasa.

1266
01:03:10,333 --> 01:03:12,416
She is the light
my mother spoke of.

1267
01:03:12,583 --> 01:03:14,083
- What?
- She's special.

1268
01:03:14,250 --> 01:03:16,750
The most amazing female
I've ever met in my life.

1269
01:03:16,916 --> 01:03:18,164
I don't know what to say to her.

1270
01:03:18,166 --> 01:03:20,000
You've spent your life
with females.

1271
01:03:20,166 --> 01:03:22,041
Please, tell me what to say.

1272
01:03:22,208 --> 01:03:24,416
Just talk to her. Be yourself.

1273
01:03:24,583 --> 01:03:25,750
[Taka] No, Mufasa.

1274
01:03:25,916 --> 01:03:26,914
[stutters] You don't understand.

1275
01:03:26,916 --> 01:03:28,375
Myself isn't good enough.

1276
01:03:28,875 --> 01:03:29,916
You...

1277
01:03:30,416 --> 01:03:32,250
just know things. [sighs]

1278
01:03:33,083 --> 01:03:34,708
Fine. Fine.

1279
01:03:35,208 --> 01:03:37,791
Keep it simple.
Ask her a question.

1280
01:03:37,958 --> 01:03:40,750
Right. A question.
This... This is good.

1281
01:03:40,916 --> 01:03:44,541
Yeah, try to be confident.
Disinterested.

1282
01:03:44,708 --> 01:03:46,208
But I'm very interested.

1283
01:03:46,375 --> 01:03:49,625
- Tell her about the flowers.
- What flowers?

1284
01:03:49,791 --> 01:03:53,250
The valley she comes from.
There's flowers everywhere.

1285
01:03:53,416 --> 01:03:55,375
They're called duck flowers.

1286
01:03:55,541 --> 01:03:57,166
Long stems.

1287
01:03:57,333 --> 01:03:59,500
It's absolutely beautiful.

1288
01:04:00,208 --> 01:04:01,208
How do you know that?

1289
01:04:01,375 --> 01:04:04,416
When she passes,
I can smell them on her fur.

1290
01:04:04,875 --> 01:04:05,875
[Taka] Okay.

1291
01:04:06,333 --> 01:04:08,583
Flowers. Disinterested.

1292
01:04:08,750 --> 01:04:10,081
- Flowers. And disinterested.
- And here's the most

1293
01:04:10,083 --> 01:04:11,500
- important thing, okay?
- [whispering] Flowers.

1294
01:04:11,666 --> 01:04:12,833
- And disinterested.
- Listen...

1295
01:04:13,000 --> 01:04:14,664
- Flowers and disinterested.
- ...when she speaks.

1296
01:04:14,666 --> 01:04:15,873
Males have trouble
with that one.

1297
01:04:15,875 --> 01:04:16,956
Flowers...

1298
01:04:16,958 --> 01:04:19,541
[in normal voice] Sorry.
What did you say?

1299
01:04:21,125 --> 01:04:22,458
- Really?
- [laughing]

1300
01:04:23,208 --> 01:04:24,791
I heard you, brother.

1301
01:04:25,416 --> 01:04:27,166
I'm gonna make you proud.

1302
01:04:28,750 --> 01:04:30,750
[♪ amusing music playing]

1303
01:04:35,375 --> 01:04:36,625
[Taka exhales]

1304
01:04:37,833 --> 01:04:40,833
[sighs] It's very hot, isn't it?

1305
01:04:41,291 --> 01:04:42,291
Yep.

1306
01:04:43,666 --> 01:04:46,750
[exhales] I...
I love listening.

1307
01:04:46,916 --> 01:04:48,041
Okay. [chuckles softly]

1308
01:04:48,208 --> 01:04:50,123
- I'm listening right now.
- To what?

1309
01:04:50,125 --> 01:04:51,206
What you just said.

1310
01:04:51,208 --> 01:04:52,289
You're the one that's talking.

1311
01:04:52,291 --> 01:04:53,375
I am.

1312
01:04:54,666 --> 01:04:56,166
- You smell like a duck.
- What?

1313
01:04:56,333 --> 01:04:57,331
Flower.

1314
01:04:57,333 --> 01:04:59,791
Uh... A duck flower.

1315
01:04:59,958 --> 01:05:02,081
[stutters] How do you know
about those flowers?

1316
01:05:02,083 --> 01:05:03,373
I, uh...

1317
01:05:03,375 --> 01:05:05,291
Well, I inhaled you
with my nose.

1318
01:05:05,458 --> 01:05:06,958
I can smell them.

1319
01:05:07,125 --> 01:05:09,750
[exhales] That's amazing.

1320
01:05:09,916 --> 01:05:11,958
Our valley was
full of those flowers,

1321
01:05:12,125 --> 01:05:15,039
thousands of them
as far as the eye could see.

1322
01:05:15,041 --> 01:05:18,375
It was... It was the most
beautiful place, Taka.

1323
01:05:19,041 --> 01:05:21,041
Did he just say
she smells like a duck?

1324
01:05:21,208 --> 01:05:23,708
And you call me a baboon?
[scoffs]

1325
01:05:24,625 --> 01:05:25,625
[fly buzzing]

1326
01:05:28,583 --> 01:05:31,250
- [♪ intriguing music playing]
- [fly buzzes]

1327
01:05:32,375 --> 01:05:33,791
[elephants trumpeting]

1328
01:05:38,625 --> 01:05:40,208
They shouldn't be here.

1329
01:05:40,541 --> 01:05:42,041
The migration patterns
are broken.

1330
01:05:42,208 --> 01:05:43,666
- I... I don't understand...
- Outsiders!

1331
01:05:43,833 --> 01:05:46,291
This is not a drill!
Just to be clear,

1332
01:05:46,500 --> 01:05:49,291
I never signed up for this.

1333
01:05:51,083 --> 01:05:52,958
It's okay. We're safe.

1334
01:05:53,125 --> 01:05:54,500
They're on the other side.

1335
01:05:55,291 --> 01:05:56,291
Nope!

1336
01:05:56,458 --> 01:05:57,916
They can just jump across!

1337
01:05:58,083 --> 01:05:59,541
[stutters] We are trapped!

1338
01:05:59,708 --> 01:06:00,833
What do we do?

1339
01:06:01,000 --> 01:06:02,375
The elephants
will fight with us.

1340
01:06:02,541 --> 01:06:03,541
And why would they do that?

1341
01:06:03,708 --> 01:06:06,125
Because I'm going to ask them.

1342
01:06:06,291 --> 01:06:07,666
Got a better idea?

1343
01:06:08,625 --> 01:06:10,666
[Sarabi] Yes,
Mr. Ask-Questions-First.

1344
01:06:10,833 --> 01:06:11,875
Get ready to run.

1345
01:06:12,416 --> 01:06:13,414
[Mufasa] Uh...

1346
01:06:13,416 --> 01:06:14,833
Where is she going?

1347
01:06:15,000 --> 01:06:17,750
Hello? Listen to me, please.
We need your help.

1348
01:06:18,000 --> 01:06:19,289
Can you talk with me?

1349
01:06:19,291 --> 01:06:20,706
- We need your help. Please.
- [trumpets]

1350
01:06:20,708 --> 01:06:21,833
[growling]

1351
01:06:22,250 --> 01:06:23,583
[Zazu] They're coming!

1352
01:06:24,416 --> 01:06:26,583
Sarabi! Sarabi, wait!

1353
01:06:26,750 --> 01:06:29,250
Sarabi! Sarabi, wait. Wait!
Where is she going?

1354
01:06:31,291 --> 01:06:33,166
She's going for the hive!

1355
01:06:33,333 --> 01:06:36,833
Like I said, get ready to run!

1356
01:06:38,333 --> 01:06:39,708
[grunts]

1357
01:06:44,333 --> 01:06:45,831
[buzzing]

1358
01:06:45,833 --> 01:06:47,416
[elephants trumpet]

1359
01:06:48,833 --> 01:06:50,041
Run!

1360
01:06:50,208 --> 01:06:52,125
Get to the trees!

1361
01:06:52,291 --> 01:06:56,083
Why am I running?

1362
01:06:57,750 --> 01:06:58,998
[elephant groans]

1363
01:06:59,000 --> 01:07:01,458
[♪ dramatic music playing]

1364
01:07:06,583 --> 01:07:07,833
[pants]

1365
01:07:09,458 --> 01:07:10,625
[grunts]

1366
01:07:12,500 --> 01:07:13,541
[elephant grunts]

1367
01:07:23,041 --> 01:07:25,083
[Zazu] Uh, Your Highness,
hold on!

1368
01:07:25,625 --> 01:07:27,833
Zazu! [screams]

1369
01:07:28,750 --> 01:07:29,833
[grunts]

1370
01:07:36,291 --> 01:07:37,748
Sarabi!

1371
01:07:37,750 --> 01:07:39,250
[gasps]

1372
01:07:40,708 --> 01:07:42,083
[growling]

1373
01:07:51,250 --> 01:07:53,166
Stand your ground!

1374
01:07:53,333 --> 01:07:54,914
Do not retreat!

1375
01:07:54,916 --> 01:07:56,583
[elephants trumpeting]

1376
01:08:02,708 --> 01:08:04,041
[growls]

1377
01:08:10,250 --> 01:08:11,333
[grunts]

1378
01:08:12,791 --> 01:08:14,583
[breathing heavily] I got you.

1379
01:08:15,208 --> 01:08:16,207
I got you.

1380
01:08:16,791 --> 01:08:19,291
Oh, Sarabi, I got you.

1381
01:08:21,666 --> 01:08:22,832
[roars]

1382
01:08:26,416 --> 01:08:29,414
That's right.
Run along, little kitty cats.

1383
01:08:29,416 --> 01:08:30,666
[meows]

1384
01:08:31,707 --> 01:08:34,207
Thank you, my friend.

1385
01:08:35,666 --> 01:08:37,082
[yelps]

1386
01:08:45,082 --> 01:08:47,707
[sighs] Ah! [chuckles]

1387
01:08:52,041 --> 01:08:53,332
[Mufasa] Over here.

1388
01:08:59,625 --> 01:09:01,250
[Rafiki] Ah...

1389
01:09:02,750 --> 01:09:04,207
Mmm...

1390
01:09:06,082 --> 01:09:10,666
<i>Vuta Pumzi.</i> Sarabi. [blows]

1391
01:09:15,625 --> 01:09:19,041
- [coughing]
- [Rafiki] Alive. She's alive!

1392
01:09:21,166 --> 01:09:22,250
[gasps]

1393
01:09:24,457 --> 01:09:26,000
Why are you all looking at me?

1394
01:09:26,166 --> 01:09:28,332
You were thrown from the tree.

1395
01:09:28,500 --> 01:09:30,666
He saved your life.

1396
01:09:31,707 --> 01:09:33,750
- Who?
- Taka.

1397
01:09:33,875 --> 01:09:36,332
- [gasps] Uh...
- Taka saved you.

1398
01:09:36,500 --> 01:09:38,375
Isn't that right, brother?

1399
01:09:41,916 --> 01:09:43,414
You saved me?

1400
01:09:43,416 --> 01:09:46,750
Uh... Well, I...
I had to do something.

1401
01:09:46,916 --> 01:09:48,082
Thank you.

1402
01:09:49,457 --> 01:09:50,707
[Mufasa] We're lucky.

1403
01:09:50,875 --> 01:09:53,125
Those bees almost killed us all.

1404
01:09:53,291 --> 01:09:54,875
Those bees saved our lives.

1405
01:09:55,041 --> 01:09:56,457
- Oh, Mufasa.
- [Mufasa] Really?

1406
01:09:56,625 --> 01:09:59,291
Because, uh, it felt like
an elephant stampede.

1407
01:09:59,457 --> 01:10:00,539
We're alive, aren't we?

1408
01:10:00,541 --> 01:10:01,707
[Mufasa] The elephants
would have fought with us.

1409
01:10:01,875 --> 01:10:02,916
[Sarabi] We're lions.

1410
01:10:03,082 --> 01:10:04,332
Nobody will fight with us.

1411
01:10:04,500 --> 01:10:05,666
Not out here.

1412
01:10:06,250 --> 01:10:07,248
[Rafiki] <i>♪ Ngiya... ♪</i>

1413
01:10:07,250 --> 01:10:08,373
[gasps]

1414
01:10:08,375 --> 01:10:10,373
<i>♪ Milele... ♪</i>

1415
01:10:10,375 --> 01:10:13,248
<i>♪ Umfoweth'ungimele ♪</i> [laughs]

1416
01:10:13,250 --> 01:10:14,414
<i>♪ Umfoweth'ungimele ♪</i>

1417
01:10:14,416 --> 01:10:15,707
Where's he going?

1418
01:10:16,625 --> 01:10:19,416
- Beyond the horizon itself.
- [sighs]

1419
01:10:19,541 --> 01:10:21,625
[Rafiki]
<i>♪ Umfoweth'ungimele... ♪</i>

1420
01:10:22,250 --> 01:10:24,207
Mufasa, thank you.

1421
01:10:29,500 --> 01:10:32,500
- [thunder rumbling]
- [♪ pensive music playing]

1422
01:10:37,707 --> 01:10:39,582
Rafiki, who...

1423
01:10:39,582 --> 01:10:41,875
Who are the Outsiders?

1424
01:10:42,041 --> 01:10:45,166
Well, the Outsiders come
from many prides.

1425
01:10:45,375 --> 01:10:47,957
But, when they are born,
they are hated

1426
01:10:47,957 --> 01:10:50,832
because they are different
from their tribe.

1427
01:10:51,000 --> 01:10:52,375
Like you and your tribe?

1428
01:10:52,541 --> 01:10:54,125
Yes, just like me.

1429
01:10:54,291 --> 01:10:56,457
- But, Rafiki?
- Yes?

1430
01:10:56,625 --> 01:10:58,541
Why do they wanna
hurt everybody?

1431
01:10:58,875 --> 01:11:02,666
Sometimes, when the people
most like you don't love you,

1432
01:11:02,832 --> 01:11:06,041
it is a hurt that can cause
the greatest pain.

1433
01:11:06,375 --> 01:11:07,707
And this pain

1434
01:11:07,875 --> 01:11:11,250
can lead you to hate everything.

1435
01:11:11,416 --> 01:11:14,000
I'm glad that didn't happen
to you, Rafiki.

1436
01:11:14,166 --> 01:11:16,707
- Yes, my child. I'm glad too.
- [chuckles softly]

1437
01:11:18,207 --> 01:11:19,332
Um, hi. We're here, too.

1438
01:11:19,500 --> 01:11:21,250
Yeah, why are you leavin' us
outside this story

1439
01:11:21,416 --> 01:11:24,039
when I'm pretty sure
we are the ultimate outsiders.

1440
01:11:24,041 --> 01:11:25,123
- Come on!
- [Timon] Yeah,

1441
01:11:25,125 --> 01:11:26,250
we've always been misunderstood.

1442
01:11:26,500 --> 01:11:27,832
I contain multitudes.

1443
01:11:33,625 --> 01:11:36,250
There are many ways to <i>Milele.</i>

1444
01:11:37,125 --> 01:11:39,332
But this will be ours.

1445
01:11:39,332 --> 01:11:41,416
[♪ mystical music playing]

1446
01:11:47,541 --> 01:11:50,166
[Eshe] <i>Go. Go, Mufasa.</i>

1447
01:11:50,582 --> 01:11:52,416
<i>Find your forever.</i>

1448
01:11:53,666 --> 01:11:55,375
[Mufasa] <i>I got you.</i>

1449
01:11:55,541 --> 01:11:57,707
Oh, Sarabi, I got you.

1450
01:11:57,875 --> 01:11:59,166
[gasping]

1451
01:12:01,166 --> 01:12:02,541
[Rafiki] Mmm.

1452
01:12:03,207 --> 01:12:08,207
<i>Iketle Rafiki.
Iketle mosimane.</i>

1453
01:12:09,541 --> 01:12:10,875
Mmm...

1454
01:12:11,000 --> 01:12:13,000
[♪ serene music playing]

1455
01:12:17,666 --> 01:12:19,082
[Mufasa] Hey, Rafiki?

1456
01:12:19,832 --> 01:12:21,000
What are you doing?

1457
01:12:21,166 --> 01:12:24,625
I am confirming
my vision, Mufasa.

1458
01:12:26,625 --> 01:12:29,664
[sighs] Can I ask you
something, Rafiki?

1459
01:12:29,666 --> 01:12:30,748
[Rafiki] Hmm?

1460
01:12:30,750 --> 01:12:33,125
How many of your visions
have come true?

1461
01:12:33,666 --> 01:12:36,166
- So far, none.
- None?

1462
01:12:36,332 --> 01:12:39,416
But it's not what I see.
It's what I feel.

1463
01:12:39,707 --> 01:12:41,291
But how do you...

1464
01:12:41,791 --> 01:12:44,416
How do you know when
you should follow a feeling?

1465
01:12:44,875 --> 01:12:46,750
<i>Milele</i> exists.

1466
01:12:47,125 --> 01:12:49,582
I feel it in here.

1467
01:12:49,916 --> 01:12:51,250
The question is,

1468
01:12:51,416 --> 01:12:53,791
what do you feel, Mufasa,

1469
01:12:55,000 --> 01:12:56,416
in there?

1470
01:13:15,957 --> 01:13:17,000
The weather's shifted.

1471
01:13:17,166 --> 01:13:18,832
There's not enough fresh snow.

1472
01:13:19,291 --> 01:13:21,414
Hey, if the Outsiders
find our tracks,

1473
01:13:21,416 --> 01:13:23,457
they'll follow them to <i>Milele.</i>

1474
01:13:23,625 --> 01:13:26,164
Zazu, only you can help us now.

1475
01:13:26,166 --> 01:13:28,125
Oh. Are you quite sure
about that?

1476
01:13:28,291 --> 01:13:29,332
No, I was actually thinking

1477
01:13:29,500 --> 01:13:31,082
that Rafiki looks pretty
handy, and with the stick...

1478
01:13:31,375 --> 01:13:32,625
Zazu, you can use your wings

1479
01:13:32,791 --> 01:13:34,457
to cover our tracks
as we head up the mountain

1480
01:13:34,625 --> 01:13:36,000
without leaving a trace.

1481
01:13:36,166 --> 01:13:38,082
Hey, you can do this.

1482
01:13:38,082 --> 01:13:40,082
Oh, hmm. Yeah.

1483
01:13:40,250 --> 01:13:42,375
Yes, sir. You're right.
I've got this.

1484
01:13:46,082 --> 01:13:48,457
Okay. It's just me against
a frozen mountain.

1485
01:13:48,625 --> 01:13:51,289
You know, one hornbill charged
with saving the future...

1486
01:13:51,291 --> 01:13:53,207
Whoa! Mummy!

1487
01:13:54,291 --> 01:13:57,375
[exclaims] Oh, man alive,
that's cold.

1488
01:14:07,125 --> 01:14:08,375
[gasps softly]

1489
01:14:10,957 --> 01:14:12,916
[Kiros growls]
Now what's happening?

1490
01:14:13,082 --> 01:14:15,125
We can't keep stopping.

1491
01:14:15,291 --> 01:14:17,666
Somehow, they have
covered their tracks.

1492
01:14:17,832 --> 01:14:19,250
In the snow?

1493
01:14:19,832 --> 01:14:21,041
It's not possible.

1494
01:14:21,207 --> 01:14:23,375
Majesty, they could be
anywhere on this mountain...

1495
01:14:23,541 --> 01:14:24,582
[Kiros] Then find them!

1496
01:14:24,750 --> 01:14:25,791
Now.

1497
01:14:26,666 --> 01:14:27,875
<i>♪ Zazu, Zazu, Zazu ♪</i>

1498
01:14:28,041 --> 01:14:30,041
<i>♪ Zazu, Zazu! ♪</i>

1499
01:14:34,957 --> 01:14:36,207
I have a report.

1500
01:14:36,375 --> 01:14:39,166
The Outsiders
are completely lost.

1501
01:14:39,332 --> 01:14:40,416
Well played, Mufasa.

1502
01:14:40,582 --> 01:14:41,750
Great job, Zazu.

1503
01:14:41,916 --> 01:14:42,916
And as per usual. [chuckles]

1504
01:14:43,082 --> 01:14:44,332
[Mufasa] I knew you could do it.

1505
01:14:44,500 --> 01:14:46,750
We did it. We did it.

1506
01:14:47,166 --> 01:14:49,291
No, you did it.

1507
01:14:49,457 --> 01:14:51,207
Great thinking, Mufasa.

1508
01:14:51,375 --> 01:14:52,707
[Zazu] Oh, we're all
rubbing off on each other.

1509
01:14:52,707 --> 01:14:53,916
Perfectly normal thing to do.

1510
01:14:54,082 --> 01:14:55,791
Who wants to rub against Zazu?

1511
01:14:55,957 --> 01:14:57,500
- [grunts]
- No one. I'm leaving now.

1512
01:14:57,666 --> 01:14:59,500
- I'll scout ahead.
- [grunts]

1513
01:15:03,166 --> 01:15:04,375
[yelps]

1514
01:15:04,500 --> 01:15:06,041
[coughs]

1515
01:15:07,166 --> 01:15:09,750
[sighs] Ah. [laughing]

1516
01:15:11,582 --> 01:15:13,125
[Mufasa laughs]

1517
01:15:13,832 --> 01:15:15,332
I got you, Rafiki.

1518
01:15:15,500 --> 01:15:16,707
- Hey.
- I got you.

1519
01:15:17,125 --> 01:15:18,125
<i>Ho monate,</i> Mufasa.

1520
01:15:18,291 --> 01:15:19,500
Yeah, I got you.

1521
01:15:23,082 --> 01:15:25,582
[gasps] Mufasa...

1522
01:15:27,041 --> 01:15:28,416
[softly] "I got you."

1523
01:15:41,291 --> 01:15:45,291
Hidden in the shadows,
downwind, light of foot.

1524
01:15:45,707 --> 01:15:47,957
Interesting hunting style,
Mufasa.

1525
01:15:48,125 --> 01:15:49,623
We have to eat something

1526
01:15:49,625 --> 01:15:51,375
before we take on that descent.

1527
01:15:51,541 --> 01:15:53,666
Unfortunately, there's
nothing to hunt up here.

1528
01:15:53,832 --> 01:15:55,000
See under that rock?

1529
01:15:55,166 --> 01:15:57,623
There's a civet
about to leave his den.

1530
01:15:57,625 --> 01:15:59,414
[chuckles] Of course
you can smell

1531
01:15:59,416 --> 01:16:00,791
a civet hidden in the snow.

1532
01:16:00,957 --> 01:16:04,039
You, the lion
who can do anything.

1533
01:16:04,041 --> 01:16:05,957
[scoffs] What's that
supposed to mean?

1534
01:16:06,125 --> 01:16:08,750
It means I see you, Mufasa.

1535
01:16:09,207 --> 01:16:10,832
I don't know
what you're talking about.

1536
01:16:11,000 --> 01:16:12,332
Now, that part, I believe.

1537
01:16:12,500 --> 01:16:14,625
Because, smart as you are,

1538
01:16:15,125 --> 01:16:17,582
you have a way of seeing
everything but yourself.

1539
01:16:17,957 --> 01:16:19,125
[Mufasa] What is this?

1540
01:16:19,582 --> 01:16:20,957
What is this, Sarabi?

1541
01:16:21,125 --> 01:16:22,789
There is a civet in the snow

1542
01:16:22,791 --> 01:16:24,416
right where you said
it would be.

1543
01:16:24,582 --> 01:16:26,500
And you smelled the Outsiders
on the wind,

1544
01:16:26,666 --> 01:16:28,957
which means you're the one who
smelled the flowers on my fur.

1545
01:16:29,125 --> 01:16:30,125
It was a lucky guess.

1546
01:16:30,291 --> 01:16:32,500
You can smell the exact flower
from my valley.

1547
01:16:32,666 --> 01:16:34,541
[chuckling] No,
that's not possible.

1548
01:16:34,707 --> 01:16:36,082
[Sarabi] You saved me.

1549
01:16:36,250 --> 01:16:38,707
Held me, covered me in the
stampede, comforted me.

1550
01:16:38,875 --> 01:16:39,875
No, it was Taka.

1551
01:16:40,041 --> 01:16:42,000
"I got you.
I got you, Sarabi."

1552
01:16:42,166 --> 01:16:44,291
- I'm here to protect him.
- That was you.

1553
01:16:44,457 --> 01:16:46,457
I was lost in the water,
and he found me.

1554
01:16:46,457 --> 01:16:47,541
My brother saved me.

1555
01:16:47,707 --> 01:16:49,207
[Sarabi] Ah, I sensed it
from the beginning.

1556
01:16:49,375 --> 01:16:51,332
His blood is the blood
of the king.

1557
01:16:51,332 --> 01:16:52,414
Mufasa.

1558
01:16:52,416 --> 01:16:54,332
- That is his destiny.
- No!

1559
01:16:54,666 --> 01:16:56,707
His destiny was to save you.

1560
01:16:56,832 --> 01:16:58,082
[grunts]

1561
01:17:00,375 --> 01:17:02,248
Now tell me it's you.

1562
01:17:02,250 --> 01:17:04,500
[♪ emotional music playing]

1563
01:17:15,375 --> 01:17:17,166
<i>♪ Ever since you appeared ♪</i>

1564
01:17:18,625 --> 01:17:21,791
<i>♪ I've been running from
something deep inside ♪</i>

1565
01:17:21,957 --> 01:17:23,625
<i>♪ And it's worse
than I feared ♪</i>

1566
01:17:25,041 --> 01:17:28,291
<i>♪ 'Cause I look in your eyes
and I can't hide ♪</i>

1567
01:17:28,457 --> 01:17:31,250
<i>- ♪ I push you away ♪
- ♪ Don't push me away ♪</i>

1568
01:17:31,416 --> 01:17:34,500
<i>♪ But the feelings come back
just twice as strong ♪</i>

1569
01:17:34,666 --> 01:17:37,625
<i>- ♪ I don't know what to say ♪
- ♪ You know just what to say ♪</i>

1570
01:17:37,791 --> 01:17:40,625
<i>♪ But I know that I'm right
where I belong ♪</i>

1571
01:17:40,791 --> 01:17:42,707
[Sarabi] <i>♪ The way you know
just where to be ♪</i>

1572
01:17:42,875 --> 01:17:43,957
<i>♪ I don't know ♪</i>

1573
01:17:43,957 --> 01:17:45,916
<i>♪ The way you move,
the way you see ♪</i>

1574
01:17:46,082 --> 01:17:47,248
<i>♪ You see me ♪</i>

1575
01:17:47,250 --> 01:17:49,500
<i>♪ The way you feel
when you're with me ♪</i>

1576
01:17:49,832 --> 01:17:51,123
<i>♪ Beside me ♪</i>

1577
01:17:51,125 --> 01:17:53,916
<i>♪ Don't hide from me anymore ♪</i>

1578
01:17:54,082 --> 01:17:56,875
<i>♪ Tell me it's you,
I know it's you ♪</i>

1579
01:17:57,041 --> 01:17:58,541
<i>♪ What do I say?
Where do I go? ♪</i>

1580
01:17:58,707 --> 01:18:00,000
<i>♪ How do I know
you feel the same? ♪</i>

1581
01:18:00,541 --> 01:18:03,166
<i>♪ Tell me it's you,
I know it's you ♪</i>

1582
01:18:03,332 --> 01:18:04,957
<i>♪ Quiet and low,
letting it go ♪</i>

1583
01:18:04,957 --> 01:18:06,125
<i>♪ Letting you know
it's in me ♪</i>

1584
01:18:06,541 --> 01:18:08,666
<i>♪ Ev'rywhere that I roam ♪</i>

1585
01:18:09,791 --> 01:18:12,875
[both] <i>♪ I remind myself
not to overstay ♪</i>

1586
01:18:13,041 --> 01:18:14,875
<i>♪ Ev'ry time I find home ♪</i>

1587
01:18:16,125 --> 01:18:19,291
[both] <i>♪ Something happens
to take that home away ♪</i>

1588
01:18:19,457 --> 01:18:21,000
<i>♪ But you've seen
what I've seen ♪</i>

1589
01:18:21,166 --> 01:18:23,332
- [Sarabi] <i>♪ I see you ♪
- ♪ As you lead with ♪</i>

1590
01:18:23,500 --> 01:18:25,750
<i>♪ A strength that shines
right through ♪</i>

1591
01:18:26,041 --> 01:18:28,625
<i>♪ You move like a queen,
a true queen ♪</i>

1592
01:18:29,041 --> 01:18:32,416
<i>♪ Don't let anything take me
away from you ♪</i>

1593
01:18:32,582 --> 01:18:35,041
<i>♪ Tell me it's you,
I know it's you ♪</i>

1594
01:18:35,207 --> 01:18:36,916
[Mufasa] <i>♪ Say it again,
say it again ♪</i>

1595
01:18:37,082 --> 01:18:38,707
<i>♪ Tell me I'll always
be with you ♪</i>

1596
01:18:38,957 --> 01:18:41,666
<i>- ♪ Tell me it's you ♪</i>
- [both] <i>♪ I know it's you ♪</i>

1597
01:18:41,832 --> 01:18:43,250
[Mufasa] <i>♪ Say it again,
say it again ♪</i>

1598
01:18:43,416 --> 01:18:44,791
<i>♪ Tell me you're
always with me ♪</i>

1599
01:18:44,957 --> 01:18:46,789
<i>♪ The way you know
just where to be ♪</i>

1600
01:18:46,791 --> 01:18:47,873
<i>♪ Now I know ♪</i>

1601
01:18:47,875 --> 01:18:49,957
<i>♪ The way you move,
the way you see ♪</i>

1602
01:18:49,957 --> 01:18:51,039
<i>♪ I see you ♪</i>

1603
01:18:51,041 --> 01:18:53,291
<i>♪ The love I feel
when you're with me ♪</i>

1604
01:18:53,832 --> 01:18:56,832
[both] <i>♪ Beside me,
beside me ♪</i>

1605
01:18:57,000 --> 01:18:59,250
[Mufasa] <i>♪ Say it again,
say it again, say it again ♪</i>

1606
01:18:59,416 --> 01:19:00,875
<i>♪ Tell me the world
won't interfere ♪</i>

1607
01:19:01,041 --> 01:19:02,457
<i>♪ Say it again, say it again ♪</i>

1608
01:19:02,625 --> 01:19:04,082
<i>♪ Tell me the words
I wanna hear ♪</i>

1609
01:19:04,250 --> 01:19:05,666
<i>♪ Say it again, say it again ♪</i>

1610
01:19:05,832 --> 01:19:09,666
<i>♪ Open your eyes
and here we go ♪</i>

1611
01:19:10,957 --> 01:19:14,250
<i>♪ I know it's you ♪</i>

1612
01:19:17,375 --> 01:19:21,500
<i>♪ I know it's you ♪</i>

1613
01:19:24,832 --> 01:19:26,457
[wind howling]

1614
01:19:29,541 --> 01:19:31,541
[♪ solemn music playing]

1615
01:19:41,791 --> 01:19:43,041
[grunts]

1616
01:19:48,375 --> 01:19:53,625
<i>♪ You know I love her,
my brother ♪</i>

1617
01:19:53,791 --> 01:19:58,916
<i>♪ There's nothing we keep
from each other ♪</i>

1618
01:19:59,082 --> 01:20:02,041
<i>♪ I saved your life ♪</i>

1619
01:20:02,207 --> 01:20:07,750
<i>♪ This is how you repay me? ♪</i>

1620
01:20:10,041 --> 01:20:12,375
<i>♪ What do I do?
What does it mean? ♪</i>

1621
01:20:12,541 --> 01:20:14,791
<i>♪ How do I ever unsee
what I've seen? ♪</i>

1622
01:20:14,957 --> 01:20:17,416
<i>♪ He was my kin
She was my queen ♪</i>

1623
01:20:17,582 --> 01:20:19,207
<i>♪ Now it's broken forever
and... ♪</i>

1624
01:20:19,791 --> 01:20:22,000
<i>♪ "Tell her it's you!
She knows it's you!" ♪</i>

1625
01:20:22,166 --> 01:20:24,332
<i>♪ What did you say to her?
What did you do? ♪</i>

1626
01:20:24,500 --> 01:20:26,832
<i>♪ I'm next in line
She should be mine, ha! ♪</i>

1627
01:20:27,250 --> 01:20:28,832
<i>♪ Are the ancestors
laughing, I... ♪</i>

1628
01:20:29,375 --> 01:20:31,666
<i>♪ What would they say?
Father is gone ♪</i>

1629
01:20:31,832 --> 01:20:34,125
<i>♪ Not before giving me
strength to go on ♪</i>

1630
01:20:34,291 --> 01:20:35,625
<i>♪ He never trusted you! ♪</i>

1631
01:20:35,791 --> 01:20:38,666
<i>♪ Did he know
you'd betray me so? ♪</i>

1632
01:20:38,832 --> 01:20:41,166
<i>♪ When you were drowning
I pulled you out ♪</i>

1633
01:20:41,375 --> 01:20:43,375
<i>♪ I gave you life
which you lived in my debt! ♪</i>

1634
01:20:43,541 --> 01:20:46,000
<i>♪ Now I'm the one drowning
Tumbling down ♪</i>

1635
01:20:46,166 --> 01:20:48,207
<i>♪ Trying to escape
what I cannot forget ♪</i>

1636
01:20:48,541 --> 01:20:50,666
<i>♪ I have a brother no longer ♪</i>

1637
01:20:50,832 --> 01:20:52,291
<i>♪ It's over and done ♪</i>

1638
01:20:52,791 --> 01:20:54,414
<i>♪ Now all I have
is this shame ♪</i>

1639
01:20:54,416 --> 01:20:56,125
<i>♪ And this rage
that I can't... ♪</i>

1640
01:20:57,500 --> 01:20:58,875
<i>♪ Out... ♪</i>

1641
01:21:00,375 --> 01:21:01,625
[rumbles]

1642
01:21:07,916 --> 01:21:09,166
[grunting]

1643
01:21:19,832 --> 01:21:21,416
[growling]

1644
01:21:26,082 --> 01:21:27,332
<i>♪ ...run ♪</i>

1645
01:21:29,541 --> 01:21:30,957
[distant growl]

1646
01:21:39,125 --> 01:21:41,125
[♪ ominous music playing]

1647
01:21:43,541 --> 01:21:48,332
[Obasi] <i>Deceit is a tool
of a great king.</i>

1648
01:22:01,207 --> 01:22:02,957
[lions growling]

1649
01:22:04,625 --> 01:22:06,125
[lion laughs]

1650
01:22:07,375 --> 01:22:10,500
There wasn't much
to eat on this mountain

1651
01:22:10,791 --> 01:22:12,166
until now.

1652
01:22:13,291 --> 01:22:16,666
Tell me, how did you cover
your tracks in the snow?

1653
01:22:16,832 --> 01:22:18,291
[Taka] A bird helped us.

1654
01:22:18,457 --> 01:22:21,207
Lions getting help from a bird?

1655
01:22:21,375 --> 01:22:24,082
Just as I will help you.

1656
01:22:24,250 --> 01:22:25,832
You will help us?

1657
01:22:26,000 --> 01:22:28,832
You think we need help
from a wounded coward?

1658
01:22:29,000 --> 01:22:32,375
I may hold the blood of a king,

1659
01:22:33,125 --> 01:22:38,416
but it was Mufasa
who killed your son.

1660
01:22:38,916 --> 01:22:41,000
It was Mufasa

1661
01:22:41,166 --> 01:22:43,082
who trapped you up here,

1662
01:22:43,250 --> 01:22:46,125
outsmarted you at every turn.

1663
01:22:46,582 --> 01:22:50,332
Now I will lead you to him
and to <i>Milele.</i>

1664
01:22:50,500 --> 01:22:52,541
[growls] <i>Milele!</i>

1665
01:22:52,707 --> 01:22:57,291
<i>Milele</i> is nothing but a dream,
a vision sold to cubs.

1666
01:22:57,500 --> 01:23:00,375
Ah. Well,
tell that to the monkey.

1667
01:23:00,541 --> 01:23:02,125
He leads them to it.

1668
01:23:02,582 --> 01:23:03,707
Look at you.

1669
01:23:04,082 --> 01:23:07,082
A pack of starving wolves

1670
01:23:07,250 --> 01:23:09,375
clinging to the side
of a mountain.

1671
01:23:09,541 --> 01:23:11,166
No tracks to follow.

1672
01:23:11,332 --> 01:23:15,875
Only one chance at revenge.

1673
01:23:17,041 --> 01:23:18,041
Me!

1674
01:23:19,666 --> 01:23:20,832
Revenge...

1675
01:23:22,916 --> 01:23:24,875
What about your father?

1676
01:23:25,832 --> 01:23:27,500
Because of Mufasa,

1677
01:23:28,207 --> 01:23:29,916
I have no father.

1678
01:23:31,500 --> 01:23:32,791
He did this.

1679
01:23:35,166 --> 01:23:36,291
Yes.

1680
01:23:36,457 --> 01:23:38,082
You lost a father,

1681
01:23:38,957 --> 01:23:40,582
and I, a son.

1682
01:23:41,125 --> 01:23:43,666
Taka, will you join us?

1683
01:23:45,166 --> 01:23:48,416
Together, we can both
have our revenge.

1684
01:23:51,207 --> 01:23:52,957
It will be my pleasure...

1685
01:23:55,291 --> 01:23:56,375
King.

1686
01:24:20,416 --> 01:24:21,416
Taka!

1687
01:24:22,707 --> 01:24:24,082
Taka, where have you been?

1688
01:24:25,291 --> 01:24:26,291
Hunting.

1689
01:24:26,750 --> 01:24:28,166
I couldn't find anything,

1690
01:24:28,625 --> 01:24:30,457
but I was never as good as you.

1691
01:24:31,291 --> 01:24:32,666
Or my mother.

1692
01:24:35,082 --> 01:24:36,123
There's something I need
to tell you.

1693
01:24:36,125 --> 01:24:37,207
No.

1694
01:24:37,750 --> 01:24:40,082
There's something
I need to tell you.

1695
01:24:40,666 --> 01:24:42,375
I need to thank you.

1696
01:24:42,541 --> 01:24:45,457
You kept your word
to Eshe and Obasi.

1697
01:24:45,625 --> 01:24:47,707
- Taka...
- You saved me, Mufasa.

1698
01:24:48,375 --> 01:24:49,541
And I...

1699
01:24:50,375 --> 01:24:54,875
will never forget
what you've done, my brother.

1700
01:24:57,291 --> 01:25:00,289
Oh, guys!
I have found a way down

1701
01:25:00,291 --> 01:25:02,125
just beyond those near peaks.

1702
01:25:03,582 --> 01:25:05,000
Was it something I said?

1703
01:25:06,582 --> 01:25:07,832
[exclaims]

1704
01:25:15,832 --> 01:25:16,832
Hey, Rafiki?

1705
01:25:17,000 --> 01:25:18,707
Yes.

1706
01:25:18,875 --> 01:25:21,375
We are nearing destiny, Mufasa.

1707
01:25:21,541 --> 01:25:24,250
And so, the earth must shake.

1708
01:25:27,832 --> 01:25:29,832
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

1709
01:25:43,082 --> 01:25:46,373
[Pumbaa] Okay, now I am
100 million percent sure

1710
01:25:46,375 --> 01:25:47,457
who Taka is.

1711
01:25:47,457 --> 01:25:48,541
Just be honest. Is it me?

1712
01:25:48,666 --> 01:25:51,125
In case you missed it,
we're not featured in this.

1713
01:25:51,291 --> 01:25:52,750
I think the civet has more
screen time.

1714
01:25:52,916 --> 01:25:54,332
Hey, maybe they'll put us
in the play.

1715
01:25:54,332 --> 01:25:55,875
No, no, please don't
mention the play again.

1716
01:25:56,041 --> 01:25:57,623
[stutters] I went to see it.
I'm nothing

1717
01:25:57,625 --> 01:25:58,750
- but a giant sock puppet.
- [gasps]

1718
01:25:58,916 --> 01:26:00,207
You went to see it?
You didn't bring me?

1719
01:26:00,375 --> 01:26:03,250
Rafiki, Mufasa and Sarabi
are in love?

1720
01:26:03,416 --> 01:26:05,207
[shudders] Love?

1721
01:26:05,375 --> 01:26:06,664
That sounds gross
and not something like

1722
01:26:06,666 --> 01:26:08,541
I constantly
think about and really want.

1723
01:26:08,707 --> 01:26:10,250
What is Taka gonna do to them?

1724
01:26:10,416 --> 01:26:13,666
Little one,
Taka's heart was broken.

1725
01:26:13,832 --> 01:26:16,707
And now his trap was set.

1726
01:26:23,250 --> 01:26:25,250
[♪ enchanting music playing]

1727
01:26:32,541 --> 01:26:34,541
Mufasa. Do you see?

1728
01:26:34,916 --> 01:26:36,457
[Sarabi] I don't believe it.

1729
01:26:37,125 --> 01:26:38,707
[Mufasa] The other side
of the light.

1730
01:26:39,375 --> 01:26:40,375
[Sarabi] Home.

1731
01:26:41,207 --> 01:26:43,041
<i>Milele.</i>

1732
01:26:44,541 --> 01:26:46,541
[♪ chorus singing
in other language]

1733
01:26:54,750 --> 01:26:56,750
[♪ enchanting music continues]

1734
01:27:13,416 --> 01:27:14,416
[grunting]

1735
01:27:20,041 --> 01:27:21,207
[lions laughing]

1736
01:27:26,207 --> 01:27:28,125
[exclaiming in other language,
laughing]

1737
01:27:33,541 --> 01:27:34,541
[Mufasa in English]
I can't believe it.

1738
01:27:35,457 --> 01:27:38,957
We found it. We found <i>Milele.</i>

1739
01:27:39,125 --> 01:27:40,125
[Taka] Yes.

1740
01:27:40,916 --> 01:27:45,416
You found it, brother.
You always do.

1741
01:27:45,541 --> 01:27:46,916
[Rafiki continues exclaiming]

1742
01:27:52,250 --> 01:27:53,332
[laughing]

1743
01:27:56,250 --> 01:27:58,250
[♪ triumphant music playing]

1744
01:28:25,250 --> 01:28:26,291
[Mufasa] Rafiki.

1745
01:28:28,207 --> 01:28:30,957
This is the tree
from your visions.

1746
01:28:33,041 --> 01:28:35,375
I have seen this tree
many times,

1747
01:28:35,582 --> 01:28:38,832
and, in each vision,
there was always a brother

1748
01:28:39,332 --> 01:28:40,957
standing right here.

1749
01:28:41,125 --> 01:28:42,666
[Mufasa] But there's
no one here, Rafiki,

1750
01:28:42,832 --> 01:28:45,625
and you came here
to find your twin.

1751
01:28:46,332 --> 01:28:48,707
He was taken from me long ago.

1752
01:28:48,875 --> 01:28:51,875
What I saw in my dreams
was a brother.

1753
01:28:52,207 --> 01:28:54,082
Standing right here.

1754
01:28:54,250 --> 01:28:56,957
A friend, family.

1755
01:28:57,125 --> 01:28:58,832
What I saw was you.

1756
01:28:59,000 --> 01:29:00,500
The unseeable.

1757
01:29:00,666 --> 01:29:03,125
I saw Mufasa.

1758
01:29:03,291 --> 01:29:04,291
Me?

1759
01:29:04,457 --> 01:29:06,291
Yes, you.

1760
01:29:06,457 --> 01:29:08,041
My brother.

1761
01:29:09,332 --> 01:29:10,791
[animals clamoring]

1762
01:29:14,125 --> 01:29:15,166
Mufasa.

1763
01:29:15,332 --> 01:29:16,750
How do you know who I am?

1764
01:29:16,916 --> 01:29:18,707
We know the Outsiders
are hunting you,

1765
01:29:18,707 --> 01:29:20,707
and we fear you'll bring danger.

1766
01:29:20,875 --> 01:29:22,875
No. No. We covered our tracks.

1767
01:29:23,250 --> 01:29:25,250
I promise you
<i>Milele</i> is a safe place,

1768
01:29:25,416 --> 01:29:28,039
and I would never do anything
to jeopardize that.

1769
01:29:28,041 --> 01:29:29,582
[Kiros roars]

1770
01:29:31,125 --> 01:29:34,000
Do not run.

1771
01:29:34,166 --> 01:29:36,207
You have nothing to fear.

1772
01:29:36,375 --> 01:29:38,166
We are not here for you.

1773
01:29:38,625 --> 01:29:41,707
We have come for Mufasa.

1774
01:29:41,875 --> 01:29:44,166
Oh, no, no.
How did they get here?

1775
01:29:45,166 --> 01:29:47,416
Do not let him divide us.

1776
01:29:48,416 --> 01:29:49,666
[animals exclaiming]

1777
01:29:50,791 --> 01:29:51,957
[laughs]

1778
01:29:52,875 --> 01:29:56,000
It's no use, Mufasa.
The Circle...

1779
01:29:57,707 --> 01:29:59,832
The Circle is broken.

1780
01:30:00,125 --> 01:30:01,123
No!

1781
01:30:01,125 --> 01:30:02,666
Mufasa, what are you doing?

1782
01:30:02,832 --> 01:30:04,998
I'm going to fight,
and I'm going to show them

1783
01:30:05,000 --> 01:30:06,166
that they can fight, too.

1784
01:30:06,750 --> 01:30:08,707
Rafiki, when you hear my signal,

1785
01:30:08,707 --> 01:30:09,791
help me call them together.

1786
01:30:09,916 --> 01:30:11,207
Yes, my brother.

1787
01:30:13,041 --> 01:30:15,041
[Kiros] There are
other lions here.

1788
01:30:15,207 --> 01:30:16,332
Find them.

1789
01:30:16,500 --> 01:30:18,582
With pleasure, Your Majesty.

1790
01:30:20,000 --> 01:30:21,666
Mufasa, you're not alone.

1791
01:30:21,832 --> 01:30:24,291
It's my turn to go
ask questions first.

1792
01:30:26,957 --> 01:30:28,082
[Kiros growls]

1793
01:30:29,457 --> 01:30:30,750
[roars]

1794
01:30:37,957 --> 01:30:41,541
This is where the hunt ends,
Mufasa. [laughs]

1795
01:30:42,541 --> 01:30:44,125
Thanks to your brother.

1796
01:30:44,291 --> 01:30:46,666
He left a trail of scars
for us to follow.

1797
01:30:46,832 --> 01:30:48,875
He made a deal to save himself.

1798
01:30:49,041 --> 01:30:51,791
- Gave us this kingdom.
- Tell me he's lying.

1799
01:30:51,957 --> 01:30:53,500
Asked us to kill the stray.

1800
01:30:53,666 --> 01:30:54,832
Taka, please!

1801
01:30:55,000 --> 01:30:57,041
I'm the son of a king.

1802
01:30:57,625 --> 01:30:59,625
But Sarabi chose you.

1803
01:30:59,791 --> 01:31:01,166
Just like Mother.

1804
01:31:01,332 --> 01:31:03,582
Just like my own father.

1805
01:31:03,750 --> 01:31:06,957
I saved you and you betrayed me!

1806
01:31:07,125 --> 01:31:08,582
What have you done?

1807
01:31:08,750 --> 01:31:10,416
I'm your brother, fight with me!

1808
01:31:10,582 --> 01:31:13,207
You stole my destiny.

1809
01:31:13,375 --> 01:31:15,000
Now this is yours.

1810
01:31:16,791 --> 01:31:18,666
He's one of us now.

1811
01:31:19,207 --> 01:31:21,000
My son's name...

1812
01:31:21,916 --> 01:31:23,291
was Shaju.

1813
01:31:24,291 --> 01:31:25,832
Shaju!

1814
01:31:26,375 --> 01:31:28,416
All of this
should have been his.

1815
01:31:28,582 --> 01:31:33,082
And now I will rule it
without mercy.

1816
01:31:33,625 --> 01:31:34,707
[growls]

1817
01:31:36,541 --> 01:31:37,541
[chuckles]

1818
01:31:39,541 --> 01:31:41,832
This one is mine.

1819
01:31:43,041 --> 01:31:44,416
[roars]

1820
01:31:44,582 --> 01:31:47,000
[♪ dramatic music playing]

1821
01:31:53,125 --> 01:31:54,332
[growling]

1822
01:31:59,666 --> 01:32:00,666
[groans]

1823
01:32:08,916 --> 01:32:09,957
[exclaims]

1824
01:32:15,666 --> 01:32:16,666
[grunts]

1825
01:32:27,750 --> 01:32:30,875
Please. We can't wage
this battle alone.

1826
01:32:31,041 --> 01:32:32,291
There's nothing we can do.

1827
01:32:32,457 --> 01:32:34,625
They've chased us
from our pride lands before.

1828
01:32:34,791 --> 01:32:36,707
- They're too strong.
- Fight with us.

1829
01:32:36,875 --> 01:32:39,375
Fight for your young.
For your future.

1830
01:32:39,541 --> 01:32:42,166
What future?
They've taken all we have.

1831
01:32:42,332 --> 01:32:44,375
And they will always take more.

1832
01:32:44,500 --> 01:32:45,666
[lions growling]

1833
01:32:51,750 --> 01:32:52,791
[roars]

1834
01:32:54,541 --> 01:32:56,541
[♪ dramatic music continues]

1835
01:33:09,332 --> 01:33:12,125
I am Mufasa,
a stray with no pride,

1836
01:33:12,291 --> 01:33:14,125
and yet I stand before you.

1837
01:33:14,291 --> 01:33:15,332
Head unbowed.

1838
01:33:15,500 --> 01:33:17,707
I know you're afraid,
but trust me.

1839
01:33:17,875 --> 01:33:20,332
Nothing will change
if we remain isolated

1840
01:33:20,332 --> 01:33:21,875
to our own tribes

1841
01:33:22,041 --> 01:33:24,666
without concern
for the fate of others.

1842
01:33:24,832 --> 01:33:26,625
But why should
we stand with you?

1843
01:33:26,791 --> 01:33:28,541
This is your fight.

1844
01:33:28,832 --> 01:33:31,625
Today, they are here for us
lions, but I assure you,

1845
01:33:31,791 --> 01:33:34,707
as you let them walk among you
in search of us now,

1846
01:33:34,875 --> 01:33:37,582
they are plotting to come
for you tomorrow.

1847
01:33:37,750 --> 01:33:40,791
One lion's hope cannot change
the fate of <i>Milele.</i>

1848
01:33:40,957 --> 01:33:43,457
There is no lion as large
as an elephant,

1849
01:33:43,457 --> 01:33:44,916
as strong as an oxen,

1850
01:33:45,082 --> 01:33:47,541
fast as a cheetah
or tall as a giraffe,

1851
01:33:47,707 --> 01:33:50,125
who can soar and scout
as wide and far

1852
01:33:50,291 --> 01:33:52,207
as the cranes
and hawks in the sky.

1853
01:33:52,416 --> 01:33:54,416
So, can't you see...

1854
01:33:54,750 --> 01:33:57,416
Every being has a place
in the Circle of Life.

1855
01:33:57,582 --> 01:33:59,375
My breath is your breath.

1856
01:33:59,541 --> 01:34:01,500
Your fight is my fight.

1857
01:34:01,666 --> 01:34:05,041
I will not bend to evil,
and neither should you.

1858
01:34:05,291 --> 01:34:07,541
<i>Nants ingonyama bagithi!</i>

1859
01:34:08,666 --> 01:34:11,207
<i>Nants ingonyama bagithi!</i>

1860
01:34:11,375 --> 01:34:14,416
<i>Nants ingonyama bagithi!</i>

1861
01:34:14,541 --> 01:34:16,207
Mufasa is right.

1862
01:34:16,500 --> 01:34:18,041
<i>Milele</i> is home.

1863
01:34:18,582 --> 01:34:22,332
We must stand with Mufasa!

1864
01:34:22,332 --> 01:34:25,000
[Rafiki] <i>Nants
ingonyama bagithi!</i>

1865
01:34:25,625 --> 01:34:29,289
Together we shall stand strong
for <i>Milele!</i>

1866
01:34:29,291 --> 01:34:30,373
[gasps]

1867
01:34:30,375 --> 01:34:32,164
[Rafiki] <i>Nants
ingonyama bagithi!</i>

1868
01:34:32,166 --> 01:34:34,789
<i>- Nants ingonyama bagithi!</i>
- [trumpets]

1869
01:34:34,791 --> 01:34:36,000
[laughs]

1870
01:34:36,666 --> 01:34:38,832
Here comes the lion!

1871
01:34:44,791 --> 01:34:45,957
[Kiros laughs]

1872
01:34:47,375 --> 01:34:49,541
From this moment on,

1873
01:34:49,707 --> 01:34:54,332
everything the light touches
belongs to me.

1874
01:34:54,582 --> 01:34:55,957
You'll have to take it.

1875
01:34:57,082 --> 01:34:58,832
[♪ dramatic music playing]

1876
01:34:59,916 --> 01:35:01,416
[growling]

1877
01:35:21,625 --> 01:35:22,875
Bye-bye.

1878
01:35:27,332 --> 01:35:28,582
[Zazu exclaims]

1879
01:35:28,750 --> 01:35:32,498
You've messed
with the wrong hornbill!

1880
01:35:32,500 --> 01:35:33,957
[lions laughing]

1881
01:35:34,832 --> 01:35:36,875
Lunch is served.

1882
01:35:37,332 --> 01:35:40,707
Stand down! I am highly
trained and occasionally a...

1883
01:35:40,916 --> 01:35:42,291
- [yelps]
- [growls]

1884
01:35:43,250 --> 01:35:45,125
This is so embarrassing.

1885
01:35:46,500 --> 01:35:49,500
I do have wings, you know.

1886
01:35:51,832 --> 01:35:52,916
[gasps]

1887
01:35:55,625 --> 01:35:57,625
[♪ tense music playing]

1888
01:36:01,832 --> 01:36:03,166
[breathing heavily]

1889
01:36:07,082 --> 01:36:08,291
Taka!

1890
01:36:09,375 --> 01:36:12,207
Taka, please. Please!

1891
01:36:12,207 --> 01:36:14,332
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

1892
01:36:16,416 --> 01:36:18,582
[Kiros] Mufasa.

1893
01:36:18,750 --> 01:36:20,957
Mufasa.

1894
01:36:26,666 --> 01:36:27,791
[roars]

1895
01:36:37,500 --> 01:36:39,166
[both growling]

1896
01:36:47,750 --> 01:36:49,291
[bats screeching]

1897
01:37:12,457 --> 01:37:13,625
[roars]

1898
01:37:14,207 --> 01:37:15,291
[groans]

1899
01:37:16,875 --> 01:37:18,707
You dare

1900
01:37:18,916 --> 01:37:21,791
to challenge me?

1901
01:37:22,832 --> 01:37:25,166
You took my son.

1902
01:37:25,832 --> 01:37:27,791
<i>My future.</i>

1903
01:37:28,375 --> 01:37:32,291
[Eshe] <i>Taka... Taka, your
moment of courage will come.</i>

1904
01:37:35,000 --> 01:37:38,832
Blood for blood.

1905
01:37:47,166 --> 01:37:49,416
Please. Don't kill him.

1906
01:37:49,582 --> 01:37:51,250
[Kiros] I didn't kill him.

1907
01:37:51,416 --> 01:37:52,750
You did.

1908
01:37:55,875 --> 01:37:57,875
[♪ tense music playing]

1909
01:38:15,375 --> 01:38:16,375
[groans]

1910
01:38:21,916 --> 01:38:23,457
They're coming.

1911
01:38:23,957 --> 01:38:25,082
[laughs]

1912
01:38:26,041 --> 01:38:28,166
The last lions.

1913
01:38:28,332 --> 01:38:30,041
Time for their extinction,

1914
01:38:30,207 --> 01:38:32,457
and we'll start
with the youngest.

1915
01:38:33,957 --> 01:38:35,332
[growling]

1916
01:38:42,416 --> 01:38:45,082
The earth will shake.

1917
01:38:45,582 --> 01:38:46,707
[rumbling]

1918
01:38:48,707 --> 01:38:50,541
Attack!

1919
01:38:52,500 --> 01:38:54,500
[♪ dramatic music playing]

1920
01:39:04,957 --> 01:39:06,332
[all clamoring]

1921
01:39:12,207 --> 01:39:13,291
[rumbling]

1922
01:39:17,457 --> 01:39:18,582
[grunts]

1923
01:39:24,041 --> 01:39:25,625
[echoes] Mufasa.

1924
01:39:27,957 --> 01:39:29,957
[♪ surreal music playing]

1925
01:39:57,625 --> 01:39:59,250
[Eshe] <i>Close your eyes</i>

1926
01:39:59,416 --> 01:40:01,625
<i>and tell me what you hear.</i>

1927
01:40:01,791 --> 01:40:03,791
<i>What you feel.</i>

1928
01:40:22,875 --> 01:40:25,082
[♪ valiant music playing]

1929
01:40:49,707 --> 01:40:51,750
[♪ solemn music playing]

1930
01:41:05,207 --> 01:41:06,207
[grunts]

1931
01:41:20,166 --> 01:41:21,332
[growls]

1932
01:41:25,666 --> 01:41:27,375
[grunts, gasps]

1933
01:41:28,041 --> 01:41:30,041
Mufasa! [panting]

1934
01:41:47,291 --> 01:41:48,457
[growls softly]

1935
01:41:58,707 --> 01:42:00,707
[♪ serene music playing]

1936
01:42:08,332 --> 01:42:10,332
He defeated the Outsiders.

1937
01:42:10,500 --> 01:42:11,873
[animal 1] The king of <i>Milele!</i>

1938
01:42:11,875 --> 01:42:13,207
[animal 2] The king of <i>Milele!</i>

1939
01:42:13,207 --> 01:42:15,082
[all exclaiming]

1940
01:42:17,375 --> 01:42:19,625
[animal 3] Is that him?
Our king?

1941
01:42:19,750 --> 01:42:21,332
[continue exclaiming]

1942
01:42:26,291 --> 01:42:27,375
Your Highness.

1943
01:42:28,875 --> 01:42:29,873
[animal 4] The King of <i>Milele.</i>

1944
01:42:29,875 --> 01:42:31,082
[animal 5] The King of <i>Milele.</i>

1945
01:42:31,875 --> 01:42:33,166
[animal 6] The King of <i>Milele.</i>

1946
01:42:33,291 --> 01:42:34,541
[animals continue exclaiming]

1947
01:42:38,875 --> 01:42:40,375
- My king.
- Your Highness.

1948
01:42:40,541 --> 01:42:42,166
- Your Majesty.
- My king.

1949
01:42:42,332 --> 01:42:43,500
Defeated Kiros!

1950
01:42:46,916 --> 01:42:48,875
- My king.
- King?

1951
01:42:49,041 --> 01:42:51,750
No, no, I'm not king.

1952
01:42:51,916 --> 01:42:53,041
Raise your heads.

1953
01:42:53,207 --> 01:42:55,832
No. I'm just... No, no!
No more kings.

1954
01:42:56,000 --> 01:42:58,332
We are all one. Please.

1955
01:42:58,500 --> 01:43:00,625
Please. Raise your heads.

1956
01:43:00,875 --> 01:43:02,832
But, Mufasa,

1957
01:43:03,000 --> 01:43:04,957
you have brought them together.

1958
01:43:05,457 --> 01:43:07,457
You helped them see
in themselves

1959
01:43:07,457 --> 01:43:09,500
what they considered unseeable.

1960
01:43:10,166 --> 01:43:12,625
Nothing is more kingly.

1961
01:43:12,832 --> 01:43:14,875
No, Rafiki.

1962
01:43:15,041 --> 01:43:18,125
I'm not king.
I'm not royal blood.

1963
01:43:18,291 --> 01:43:20,082
Don't you see, my brother?

1964
01:43:20,541 --> 01:43:23,000
It is not what you were,

1965
01:43:23,207 --> 01:43:27,416
it is what you have become.
[chuckles]

1966
01:43:28,250 --> 01:43:31,041
The King of <i>Milele.</i>

1967
01:43:38,000 --> 01:43:39,375
My brother,

1968
01:43:39,832 --> 01:43:42,791
something beautiful awaits you.

1969
01:43:51,166 --> 01:43:52,457
[sniffing]

1970
01:43:55,250 --> 01:43:56,457
Is this real?

1971
01:43:59,916 --> 01:44:01,125
But it can't be.

1972
01:44:03,832 --> 01:44:05,250
It can't be.

1973
01:44:11,375 --> 01:44:13,375
[♪ emotional music playing]

1974
01:44:26,250 --> 01:44:28,625
[Afia whispers] Oh, Mufasa.
[gasps]

1975
01:44:29,375 --> 01:44:31,041
But how can it be?

1976
01:44:31,500 --> 01:44:34,916
I had a son named Mufasa.

1977
01:44:35,125 --> 01:44:37,916
Taken from me by a great flood.

1978
01:44:38,416 --> 01:44:39,416
- Mother?
- [gasps]

1979
01:44:41,125 --> 01:44:43,250
I never stopped hoping.

1980
01:44:43,416 --> 01:44:45,166
Believing.

1981
01:44:45,332 --> 01:44:47,000
- My son.
- [sighs]

1982
01:44:49,750 --> 01:44:51,541
I've dreamt of this moment.

1983
01:44:54,291 --> 01:44:56,000
And now it's come true.

1984
01:44:56,207 --> 01:44:57,957
Oh, Mufasa.

1985
01:45:03,082 --> 01:45:04,375
But Father?

1986
01:45:06,375 --> 01:45:07,498
Where's Father?

1987
01:45:07,500 --> 01:45:09,375
[♪ melancholic music playing]

1988
01:45:12,457 --> 01:45:13,457
[grunts softly]

1989
01:45:14,082 --> 01:45:16,041
[Afia] He lives in you now.

1990
01:45:16,957 --> 01:45:19,916
He lives in you.

1991
01:45:22,957 --> 01:45:23,957
[sighs]

1992
01:45:26,541 --> 01:45:28,916
I always dreamed
we'd be together again.

1993
01:45:30,166 --> 01:45:34,125
And I knew it would be
in <i>Milele.</i>

1994
01:45:36,166 --> 01:45:37,291
My son.

1995
01:45:38,457 --> 01:45:39,666
[Taka] Mufasa.

1996
01:45:46,625 --> 01:45:49,750
Mufasa, please forgive me.

1997
01:45:50,541 --> 01:45:53,332
You must banish him, Sire.

1998
01:45:55,166 --> 01:45:57,041
[Mufasa] As long as I am king,

1999
01:45:57,207 --> 01:45:59,666
my brother will have
a place here.

2000
01:45:59,791 --> 01:46:00,791
[gasps]

2001
01:46:01,416 --> 01:46:03,916
Brother, I am so...

2002
01:46:04,082 --> 01:46:05,916
But I won't ever

2003
01:46:06,541 --> 01:46:08,207
say your name again.

2004
01:46:09,582 --> 01:46:10,832
I can't.

2005
01:46:12,082 --> 01:46:13,291
I won't.

2006
01:46:14,125 --> 01:46:15,957
Then call me Scar.

2007
01:46:16,582 --> 01:46:19,832
So I will never forget
what I have done.

2008
01:46:20,625 --> 01:46:21,916
Scar.

2009
01:46:22,916 --> 01:46:24,625
Your Majesty.

2010
01:46:34,125 --> 01:46:35,582
[Sarabi] Welcome home.

2011
01:46:42,875 --> 01:46:44,332
Your Majesty.

2012
01:46:52,291 --> 01:46:53,875
[Rafiki] So, Mufasa,

2013
01:46:54,041 --> 01:46:56,789
I see your family
has been awaiting you

2014
01:46:56,791 --> 01:46:59,207
in <i>Milele</i> after all.

2015
01:47:00,000 --> 01:47:01,957
[chuckles] Yes, Rafiki.

2016
01:47:03,250 --> 01:47:04,582
Yes, they were.

2017
01:47:11,582 --> 01:47:14,457
It is your time, Mufasa.

2018
01:47:15,625 --> 01:47:18,041
Rafiki, I wish I could see him.

2019
01:47:18,500 --> 01:47:20,500
I wish I could meet
my grandfather.

2020
01:47:20,666 --> 01:47:23,207
As Mufasa once told your father,

2021
01:47:23,375 --> 01:47:25,457
look into the heavens, Kiara.

2022
01:47:25,625 --> 01:47:29,207
The great kings of the past
will always be there

2023
01:47:30,000 --> 01:47:31,248
waiting for you.

2024
01:47:31,250 --> 01:47:33,332
[♪ dramatic music playing]

2025
01:47:47,082 --> 01:47:48,082
[grunts]

2026
01:48:15,541 --> 01:48:17,541
[♪ triumphant music playing]

2027
01:48:24,000 --> 01:48:25,207
[roaring]

2028
01:48:33,332 --> 01:48:34,500
[roaring]

2029
01:48:53,166 --> 01:48:54,291
[gasps]

2030
01:48:55,416 --> 01:48:56,539
[roars]

2031
01:48:56,541 --> 01:48:59,041
[♪ enthralling song playing
in other language]

2032
01:49:12,750 --> 01:49:13,832
Mmm...

2033
01:49:19,125 --> 01:49:21,164
I don't want him to go, Rafiki.

2034
01:49:21,166 --> 01:49:22,707
I don't want it to end.

2035
01:49:23,291 --> 01:49:25,207
Don't you see, Kiara?

2036
01:49:25,582 --> 01:49:28,291
Mufasa lives in you.

2037
01:49:29,166 --> 01:49:31,541
He lives in you.

2038
01:49:33,791 --> 01:49:35,707
[gasps] Dad!

2039
01:49:37,082 --> 01:49:39,291
- Rafiki.
- It was unbelievable.

2040
01:49:39,457 --> 01:49:41,332
- It was perfect.
- You could not improve on it.

2041
01:49:41,500 --> 01:49:43,041
That said, I do have notes.

2042
01:49:43,207 --> 01:49:45,666
Some suggestions. Take 'em
or leave 'em. But take 'em.

2043
01:49:47,207 --> 01:49:48,914
- [Kiara] Dad!
- [Simba] Kiara!

2044
01:49:48,916 --> 01:49:50,041
[panting]

2045
01:49:51,082 --> 01:49:53,207
- [coos]
- Kiara.

2046
01:49:53,375 --> 01:49:54,375
Dad.

2047
01:49:54,791 --> 01:49:56,207
Where's Mom?

2048
01:49:56,375 --> 01:49:59,000
[chuckles] Well, love, there's
something you need to know.

2049
01:49:59,166 --> 01:50:01,375
What? Did something
happen to Mom?

2050
01:50:01,541 --> 01:50:03,832
Baby, I'm right here,
and I'm fine.

2051
01:50:04,041 --> 01:50:05,625
Where were you?

2052
01:50:05,791 --> 01:50:06,791
Kiara,

2053
01:50:06,957 --> 01:50:08,957
this is your new brother.

2054
01:50:09,125 --> 01:50:10,207
Brother?

2055
01:50:10,375 --> 01:50:11,625
I have a brother?

2056
01:50:12,582 --> 01:50:16,000
Hi there. I'm Kiara.
I will take care of you.

2057
01:50:16,541 --> 01:50:18,250
- Forever.
- [grunts]

2058
01:50:19,041 --> 01:50:20,332
Little one,

2059
01:50:20,500 --> 01:50:22,250
let me tell you a story.

2060
01:50:22,750 --> 01:50:25,500
A story of a great king.

2061
01:50:26,750 --> 01:50:28,166
[♪ music swells]

2062
01:50:42,625 --> 01:50:44,832
[♪ exhilarating song playing
in other language]

2063
01:52:31,582 --> 01:52:32,666
[song ends]

2064
01:52:32,791 --> 01:52:34,791
[♪ serene music playing]

2065
01:53:56,666 --> 01:53:58,750
[♪ whimsical music playing]

2066
01:54:47,291 --> 01:54:49,291
[♪ captivating song playing]

2067
01:55:13,375 --> 01:55:14,791
[man vocalizing]

2068
01:55:23,125 --> 01:55:24,625
[singing in other language]

2069
01:56:11,791 --> 01:56:13,166
[song ends]

2070
01:56:14,541 --> 01:56:16,541
[♪ mystical music playing]

2071
01:57:21,250 --> 01:57:23,125
[man singing in other language]

2072
01:57:51,750 --> 01:57:53,750
[♪ music fades]
